The highlight of my day was when I reached out to the 3Dimensional Institute and left a message for someone to call me regarding a question I had about my Transformational Purpose Statement.  I really didn't expect anyone to call me back until the following Monday because of the time difference.  Well, Mitch Hull calls me about ten minutes later and asks me how he can help me. I was so surprised that could barely articulate my question to him.  He was so pleasant and took the time to explain how my role in assisting the coaches is very important and shared great suggestions on how to write my statement.  He mentioned that he was happy that someone in my position within our department was interested in completing the 3Dimensional Coaching Course.  Super excited to see the updated version Mitch shared with me while I was talking with him today.  He's excited to reconnect with Rob about the new version.

3.5 out of 5 stars.  The assistance on developing a Foundational Purpose Statement was worth the price of admission.  And the course did an excellent job making me take the time to consider my coaching methods and whether I am properly balancing - for today's athletes - the effort spent on Fundamentals, Psychology, and Heart.  I appreciated the practical application examples but believe some could be improved or replaced.  Finally, I was disappointed in the proponency for the Fellowship of Christian Athletes, whose stance on LGBTQ athletes is at odds with the 3D Institute's messaging regarding the power of love and its teaching that there should be no barriers to joining the team/community.

Do not recommend unless you want to be fed lots of Christian anecdotes with little to no scientific data to back up their claims. This course is also primarily led by men and I feel does not appropriately cover how to properly train up athletes that are primarily female dominant.

I began with the 3D Essentials course, which I completed in one evening (about 2 hours) due to brisk pacing and inspiration. 
Essentials is full of teasers for "further details" promised in the full certification course.
I was initially eager for the rest of the story, but these nuggets were difficult to find buried within a 30-hour course.
This includes mostly short video clips of solo speakers. Being a visual learner, I found myself frequently distracted by the speakers' mannerisms, video quirks (arbitrary changes of camera angle) and misspellings ("dissention"?) on graphics. The speeches seem universally over-acted, as if every speaker has been coached to (patronizingly) hand-sign every phrase.
I get that this is probably intended to mimic an in-person clinic (some clips include live audiences) and I approximated this experience by completing much of this course straight through (getting in another "zone" on a cold, rainy weekend when I lacked the energy to tackle anything else).
However, the course thus fails to take advantage of additional possibilities offered by the online medium. A simple transcript, for instance, would heighten retention (via simultaneous visual and auditory learning), speed understanding of the course framework, and enable quick reference for review. It would also allow for self-paced learning, and flexibility in navigating the course. (How many of us read any other coaching manual straight through?)
There is plenty of inspiring material here! I would love to see it condensed into a more concentrated 5- or 10-hour presentation, so we could find and focus on it more quickly.

I coach to create a more positive environment and to hopefully create more positive people who can see the difference between doing something good for the sake of good and not just creating a selfish legacy so that people look back and put a plaque on a wall. For anyone who is committed to excellence in all areas of their lives, not just coaching, this is an absolute "must" course to enroll in and finish. I just completed a 42-year coaching career. I have been to a multitude of coaches' clinics: almost all are in the first and second dimension. This is the first time I have received detailed teaching in the third dimension. Capturing the heart of your athletes is the most important dimension of the three. Teaching first dimension fundamentals and second dimension psychology are critical for success. If you want to reach your full potential, as a coach, you must learn to capture an athlete's heart if you want that athlete to perform at his/her highest level. Pursuing excellence means making the most out of your God-given talent as an athlete and a human being. This course covers all of this in detail.

As a 51 year old returning College student i feel this was well worth the time i personally invested in it and what the college paid to purchase it. 
As i am finishing the course I’m  sitting emotional as tears well up in my eyes. This material, I believe bridges the gap between doing God’s will first (Matthew 6:33) and allowing people to nurture their inner child through play and sports and using their energy, especially the fight or flight energy our bodies were created with, in a positive and productive way that helps in their quest to honor their creator to teach, to be a friend and give everyone a sense and feeling of belonging, essentially what we have learned having played sports and been an athlete ourselves. Definitely, it is giving back what we were given. Jesus says it himself, “There’s more happiness in giving then there is in receiving.” We know this is in reference to the ‘word of Christ’ but it certainly paves the way for sharing that word and the love and friendship we desire ourselves. I’ve struggled for years to bridge the gap between competitive sports and Christianity, truth! In fact although having played every sport possible to stay on ‘the right path’ , before learning about the Bible truth in detail, my four sons only played maybe one sport each, except for the youngest. I was always concerned with bad association. This certainly is a great teacher, it’s amazing that it incorporates God’s word and teaching! I would have never thought it was possible. A foundation built on Gods word. How much stronger could it be ?? I often used the illustration to empower my sons to make the right choices (calculate risk/cost) that Jesus gave in Matthew 17:5, “ 
5 While he was still speaking, look! a bright cloud overshadowed them, and look! a voice out of the cloud said: “This is my Son, the beloved, whom I have approved.+ Listen to him.”
And Luke 14:28 28 For example, who of you wanting to build a tower does not first sit down and calculate the expense to see if he has enough to complete it?
Meaning if Jesus says building a foundation builds a strong tower (our future life) we can liken our future to that tower and our foundation is our education, job, place to live, a vehicle so that we may have something to contribute to a future spouse and family. 
I would say ty for all the hard work and energy put into this journey and ty personally for affecting my life in such a positive way!

column3: Head Wrestling Coach - Bentonville West High School
column7:
The 3Dimensional Coaching course was an incredible experience. It gave me a great perspective on the power of coaching through a transformational purpose. We implemented many of the strategies from the program, such as games, Spotlight Drill, home visits, banquet letters, and more over the past two seasons. It really helped our team become closer and find the joy in sport again. 

One of our athletes was recently killed in a car accident. While there's nothing that could have prepared me for this tragedy, I am grateful for my 3D Coach training. I have some peace in this tragedy, because through the implementation of the 3Dimensional strategies, my athletes shared so much love and joy with each other. It has also given me a framework to discuss this tragedy with my team, so we can grieve and heal together.

The journey thus far has been refreshing and up lifting and I commend the group of a amazing people whom are driving this. All coaches should use this opportunity to consider a change in trajectory. Salute
Thought provoking and inspiring.

I thought the course was a great reminder for going the "extra mile" for our student athletes in getting to know them in all aspects of their life (on and off the field).  It was also a great reminder why I coach and love it.  Thank You for making this course.
This course allows you to take a look at yourself, your Staff and your Program and try new things that will help elevate all of those simultaneously.

We need to see ourselves as guides for young men on their journey to develop physically, mentally, socially and spiritually.   Unless we build on a solid foundation of faith, we risk making investments that won't endure the storms of life.  3D reminds us that character counts, and that our3rd dimension, our fundamental beliefs and core values, guide our daily decision making.

I completed all my degree and post-graduate studies through online and distance learning, and in my opinion this course rates highly with regards to the manner in which it is being presented. Each component is offered independently in manageable units, yet all the material is brought together superbly to create a complete and thorough understanding of the 3D framework. I have previous experience of the methodology behind 2nd and 3rd dimension approaches to coaching, yet the material in the course kept pulling me in for more. The one element of my coaching that has been lacking throughout the years has been the aspect of my Christianity in a multi-religious, and secular coaching environment. The FCA add-on material has been extremely motivational to me on a personal level, and I am indeed glad that I selected to have the add-on included in my course. I would recommend this course to any aspiring coach or teacher, and in fact, to any person who finds themselves in a mentoring position.

As a person who is not interested in physical sports, this made most of the content feel irrelevant and unrelatable. We have multiple students on our team that are non-binary and this can often be dismissive of these students.

Our high school coaching staff was asked to embark on this journey during the COVID-19 pandemic. This program helped me reflect on how I live, influence, and learn in both my professional AND personal lives: as a teacher, coach, husband, father, son, and friend.  I would recommend this program to anyone who works with young people - even those that don't - but who wants to do better at finding balance in their life, value in personal relationships, and satisfaction in what they do.

column3: Dallas Center Grimes Head Boys Cross Country Coach -- Servant
column7: The early portions of the course are somewhat offputting due to the generalizations that happen about kids and the world.  The "entitlement" generation has been created by adults.  Adults have created what they now abhor.  As the course moved further along, the content improved.  It's a bit disconcerting to have content toward the end centered around FCA and God when that really shouldn't have anything to do with public school programming.  Even as a faithful Christian, I do not intermingle the two. My values and the way I treat people would certainly align, but it is not something I bring into our program.  I invite you to explore ways to eliminate that content or make it optional for those who want to explore it.  The third dimension is about heart, but that doesn't mean it has to involve God or faith in God.  In fact, it is important delineate between the two to best meet the needs of all coaches, athletes, and programs.  Generally speaking, this program is likely helpful to a good number of folks, especially if they complete it with integrity.
This was a great course that provided a lot of insight into athletes today and provided many strategies to implement that I believe will help with any program.

It helped me focus on my "why" as a coach. It reengaged my passion and has made me more energized, excited, and ready to be back in the gym in the role of "Coach." I'm excited to see the ways this learning will help to transform my interactions with my team, players, and community.
Great lessons & information on becoming a 3D Coach!
Great program

Being a first timer and one who has been involved in soccer coaching for quite some time, this course has given me a different perspective in both coaching players and molding coaches from the 3 Dimension approach. I love the "TO'" and "THROUGH" strategies.
It was very well done and informative course on becoming a better coach.  It helped me understand what my purpose for coaching really was.
Very interesting course with the insight of very energetic individuals.  Helps explain that one dimension of coaching that we all struggle with...HEART.
I am a big fan of this framework. I have been looking for something like this to pull it all together for nearly 10 years in my position. Congratulations to you all, and thank you!

Very helpful and was really awesome for me to do this course and i am looking forward to apply this as a new young coach into the teams that i am involved but most importantly to apply this to my family as well. Thanks for a great course.
Best class I have taken, would highly recommend to my entire staff and all coaches. Wish I would have taken it sooner in my career!

Having already read Joe Ehrmann and espousing inside-out coaching this was a nice branching off and g of some of what I already do.  Great stuff!  
I like to say that "doing the right thing is always good for business," meaning that if we coach in 3D we are putting ourselves in the best position to see excellence (so, yes,  outcome oriented there,  but,  of course, take care of the process and the outcome takes care of itself!)

I enjoyed my time listening and thinking about what I as a coach so inclued in my coaching.  I have seen things that I have done in the past that were good and even in the 2n and 3rd dimensions.  This is going to make my final year(s) of coach more meaningful.
This course is informative and practical.  I was able to take away ideas that I can use in coaching.
This is a great course for coaches. It made me look at our program and take some of the ideas and suggestions back to use with our athletes. It has created energy in me to coach differently.
Great course! The best part is I have been coaching this way and it makes me feel good to know I've been going in the right direction. Thank you all!!!
As a veteran coach of 40 years, I found this course refreshing.
I enjoyed it. It reminded me of things that I had forgot
I enjoyed it. It reminded me of things that I had forgot
Great Course, very informational!
It make coaches evaluate themselves and think deeper about their philosophies and strategies to reach athletes.
Great insight to motivate
It was very easy to follow along with. I enjoyed going through it.
Great insight to motivate

I really enjoyed this perspective on coaching and appreciated that it made me think critically about how I coach and interact with others. It was easy to follow and was accessible. I'm looking forward to not only holding myself accountable but introducing some new strategies with the teams and groups I am a part of.
This is a great course for coaches. It made me look at our program and take some of the ideas and suggestions back to use with our athletes. It has created energy in me to coach differently.

I have been involved in sports for the past 50 years as a player, coach (youth, high school, collegian). I have never experience such extensive and intense coaching course. It is exactly what today's  coaches need in their library. The course is a living library that will have a positive life changing  effect in the lives of participants, coaches, families, and the community. More importantly, the  course intentionally focuses on developing the entire youth ( spiritually, physically, academically, socially, and athletically). I highly recommend this course without any reservations.
A lot of information and very long. It's great but 25 chapters with 6 units each makes it overwhelming to try an implement as a coach. There is a lot of information to unpack before implementing.
Life changing.
Enjoyed the program. Good ideas.
Thorough examination of coaching at the 3D level with good insight on programs that can be implemented with our team.
Enjoyed the course

It s a solid coaching tool and has great resources. It is long and somewhat tedious to get through but absolutely filled with nuggets of truth and inspiration that have the power to transform coaches.

I have been a varsity coach for 39 years in 3 different varsity programs. I truly wish i had been given the opportunity to learn from this program in my earlier years. While i believe i have coached in the 3 Dimensions over much of my career, it was truly a trial and error growth. This presentation does a great job of guiding and coach to become better person, teacher, coach and friend.
I loved it. Every Coach should take this course. I will be a better coach and person.

A lot of the course content I knew before taking the course, but never put into the simple words that the instructors used.  I also never really had a plan to accomplish what I wanted to accomplish with the athletes. I just kind of made it up as I went along, hoping to achieve the relational and higher purpose strategies of the 2nd and 3rd dimensions, but without a well thought out plan.  This course gave me a lot to think about how to implement a well thought out course of action for present and future athletes, coaches, and parents that I will be working with.
This was a great course and I'll definitely impart many of the things I learned into my program.
The 3D Coaching course is an essential tool for every coach and frankly, every adult responsible for bringing up children.  Thank you!
I enjoyed taking this course and thought it was very well done from start to finish.

God blessed me in my days of playing and coaching football to be play for and coach with five coaches that were 3D coaches.  My father, Gordon McKinstrey, Shrine football coach Ed Thomas, college football coach Larry Korver, first coach I coached for, Jerry Staton, and second coach I coached for, Ron Schipper.  It is the only way I believed coaching was and how it should be.  This course reaffirmed to me that God allowed me to be blessed to learn from these men.  This course affirmed the many things we are trying to do with Pella Football and the young men we coach.  I learned a lot about the overarching themes in sport today but just did not know how to put these themes into words.  There is no doubt where Jeff Duke, Mark Hall, and Wes Simmons stand in their relationship with Jesus.  Thank you to you guys for all your work, time, and efforts in 3D coaching.  I want to finish my coaching career well and this 3D coaching class has inspired me to keep fighting to the finish.  As Steve Johnson from Bethel has said, "Get in the fight, stay in the fight, Finish!"  Thank you!!!!!!
This course was an amazing journey!

I was pleasantly surprised at the level of quality and content of this course. The faith-based add-ons were also very insightful. I would heartily recommend this course to coaches who aspire to coach the whole athlete toward beautiful and excellent outcomes.
This course helped me see that I need to focus not only on improving my athlete's abilities or even motivation but to help them create good moral standards and a sense of character.
The course is very helpful for anyone trying to develop a team community and foster youth development rather than just coach sport. Very well made and a great value.
This course is incredibly liberating. I learned a lot about my current self and the self I want to be moving forward. I highly recommend it for coaches of all ages and experience.
This course has really motivated me to create put in practice what was taught, and has given me ways to do this.
After over 25 years of coaching, there is still so much to learn from this course!

This course has given me a plethora of ideas to use in coaching.  I look forward to implementing several strategies taught in this course in upcoming seasons to help students grow not just as athletes, but as people.

Thorough, outside the box, interactive, impactful coaching course. Will change at least a little all coaches who complete course- each coach will determine how much they improve as a coach by themselves.
I really liked this course it gave me great ideas for the future of Enumclaw XC and Track.
I recommend this course to any serious minded Coach who desire greatness in their Coaching Career.
This course is mind blowing and very important to every Coach you desire greatness in Coaching.

column3: Head coach of Rugby, S. Thomas' college
column7: Oh my loads of knowledge taken and will revisit for sure. Thank you
A great refresher and encouragement to keep perspective as we try to transform lives through sport.
This course reminded me of what it truly means to be a coach as well as the influence and power that we have on kids to make them better athletes and people.

Now that I am finished with this course I cannot wait to begin to implement the strategies that I learned in this course, as well as to strengthen some of the things that I already do with my team. I also look forward to sharing many of these lessons with other coaches in our program along with other coaching colleagues.
The overall course is very inspirational.  The course applies to the generation z athlete.
I took this course in my 25th year of coaching.  Wish it was available many years ago.  I learned so much that I could have used over the years.
Very Informative.
Very inspirational!
Highly engaging.  I'm excited about starting a new journey.
This coarse was well put together, informative, and useful.
Great course, i really enjoyed it!!
excellent course

column3: Jack Young Middle School Track and Field Coach
column7: I enjoyed the introspection that this course pushed me to complete. It not only caused me to think about my coaching, but my teaching, and the way I acted in my community.

This is a transformational course that will change why you coach, how you coach, and the impact of your coaching.  I believe this should be required of anyone who wants to take the essence of coaching seriously.  It has helped me re-evaluate why I went into coaching in the first place, motivate me to be better in all areas of my coaching (especially relationships and 3rd-dimensional strategies), and given me specific strategies and examples of how to do this.  Thank you Jeff Duke and the 3D staff for an incredible resource that will make me not just a better coach but a better person and help me positively impact my teams and communities.
Thought it was very good

I liked how positive everything on here was. I work in an alternative school where many of my students struggle daily, and this really felt similar to how I teach my students; with compassion and love and building them up. While I coach in a more traditional school, I have always tried to apply my beliefs into how I coach as well.

What an eye opening experience.  I love the courses on dimension 2 and 3.  It makes me want to get out there and be a better coach. I am well versed in the first dimension, but after going through this course, I need to improve even more on D2 & 3. I am going to use the many ideas that I've learned.  I cannot wait to get out there and coach next season.
3DI has helped me self reflect and be aware of the changes I need to make within myself to make my program better.

This course is good for Coaches who wants model a leadership character that is full of truth, goodness and beauty.

This course empowers Coaches to model athletes for them to become leader modelers, peer modelers, self modelers and also influence their community positively.

3Dimensional Coaches impact more people positively in one year than 1st and 2nd Dimension Coaches does in a life time.

3Dimensional Coaches makes sports fun and enjoyable.
Great course. I would personally like more reading material and less videos. But overall, a very good course
This course definitely rejuvenated my spirit as a coach In all aspects of my life.

column3: West Valley HS (Yakima) - Head Boys Soccer Coach
column7: This course was amazing.

column3: West Valley HS Yakima - Head Boys Soccer
column7: This course was amazing.
I loved it!

Honestly, I don't know how Coaches felt prepared for the responsibility of taking on dozens or hundreds of athletes before the 3D Course. The wisdom and information shared in this course is essential for everyone who understands that coaching can shape and transform lives -- not just teach athletic skills. I would (and have already) recommend the 3D Coaching Course to all; it is loaded with golden nuggets for life well beyond the coaching arena. Thank you for partnering with FCA as well! Those additional Faith-Based words of wisdom cut straight to the heart of why integritous coaching is so important in our culture today.
Less videos, more interaction or activities that aren't wholly based on "quizzes". Overall, it is a good learning experience for coaches who wish to further develop themselves as well.
Excellent course... a must for "every" coach
Well done!
This course was informative.

column3: head girls track and field coach
column7: outstanding.
This program gives invaluable resources to coaches to promote a positive and team centered experience for all athletes.

3D Coaching was a phenomenal experience. I strongly believe that my values and virtues as a coach aligned with strategies used in the 2nd and 3rd dimensions. It reaffirmed many thoughts I had on ways to continue to improve and grow as a coach. I plan to review this content more than once, and will recommend to my future coaching staff!
I really liked it, as a coach who has been preaching this kind of stuff for years it helped to be able to put specific language to what I always knew as the best way to coach in the 3D way.

The 3D framework and structure was delivered in a way that created a process for understanding. The class assisted in reinforcing what our organizations philosophical approach is in coaching student-athletes as well as providing additional ideas and structure. But what it really did was provide us a more defined framework and language that we can plug in to what we currently employ as an organization. Thank you.
The course helped to visually lay out the values of working with student athletes.
I learned a great deal through the 3D process and it helped solidify many of my own beliefs.
It really opened my eyes to all that coaching can be, and the coaching is more than just wins and losses on the field.

It was so refreshing to have a class that was fundamentally based in faith as that does not seem to be the norm anymore.  It also made sense of many struggles and issues I've seen in coaching but couldn't put a finger on the source or reason and gave me many ideas of how to proceed to deal with those struggles. I particularly like how it challenges us coaches to deal with ourselves and our issues first as that is fundamental in bringing your best to any relationship.

This course is absolutely great and fantastic, I will recommend it for every coach in the world now. In-fact every coach in this world needs this education to transform their thinking, plans and actions in coaching career.

Coaches needs this course if they want to become great mentors of others.

Coaches needs to do this course if they really want to become great leaders as coaches who will lead in truth, in beauty, and in goodness.

If coaches really want to live a legacy by modeling athletes who will transform their community, they need to pursue this course.

I will recommend this course for coaches who want the best for their athletes and themselves.
There were alot of things I did in the 3rd dimension that I wasn't aware of.  I believe that I will grow even more now that I am aware.
I really enjoyed taking this course!
The course makes you take inventory of your life and what you truly value.  There is a lot of insight into how to connect with and encourage kids/people that you otherwise might not even attempt to.
This course made you think deeply into the "why do you coach."

This course has been exactly what I was looking for. I have been searching and reading many resources, trying to formulate my direction and purpose in coaching. I have learned a lot but have been struggling to put all that I have learned into to an organized collection of thoughts. This course did that. It organized all that I have been trying to piece together into a perfect format.
#NAME?

This is an amazing course.  I found it obtaining my Master's degree in coaching and I have really bought into the framework.  I look forward to using the strategies to help with culture and build a community in my program.  The written materials and models will help guide me to live by my transformational statement.
Got me inspired about coaching.
Outstanding research and delivery on how to reach the hearts of young athletes.  Much respect and adoration for the heartbeat behind this movement.  So needed!

I don't know how much new information was given--some of the stuff we already do and I would like information on stuff we don't do.  I wish there was a way to bypass some stuff and go deeper into other stuff.

Outstanding... I realized that for most of my coaching career I seldom got out of the 1st dimension.  I did hit 2nd and 3rd but it was inconsistently approached.  I can also take this work and apply it to my family life.

This 3D coaching course brought a whole new meaning to who I am as a coach.  Discovering techniques to use in the 2nd and 3rd dimensions were eye opening.  This course helped to breathe new life into my athletic programs and my coaching methods.  I am looking forward to the future because I now see that future in a whole new light!

THE 3D COACHING COURSE TEACHES COACHES TO BE UNIVERSAL THINKERS IN THEIR SPORT AREA AND NOT ONE DIMENSIONAL THINKERS OF WIN/LOSS. AS I WENT THROUGH THE COURSE I CONTINUALLY THOUGHT ABOUT MY MIDDLE SCHOOL PRINCIPAL DAYS. THE MIDDLE SCHOOL PHYLOSOPHY IS TOO SERVICE THE WHOLE PERSON.
Life changing
Very good coaching platform.
Awesome course.
Help the department of education realize we need God back in the classroom.
Really made me think and learn a lot about myself and my coaching style with this new generation of athletes!
Lots of work; but well worth it in the end.  Great ideas and information!
Incredible material. It really opens your eyes to all three dimensions and the significance we all have as coaches to our athletes on and off the field.

I really enjoyed the aspect of making an individual difference in a student's life on a personal level but at the same time being able to affect everyone on the same team as well. Very well brought up information and I recommend this course for coaches wanting to go the extra mile.
This course helped me develop a focus for my coaching and teaching career, putting my thoughts and focus into words to drive my development.

column3: Head Coach - Wilsonville High School Volleyball
column7: A good course and very thought provoking.

I thought this was a fantastic course that dove into a much deeper meaning of coaching. I really enjoyed the transformational purpose statement and all the different coaches that were starred in this training. Great course that i would recommend to every coach out there
Thought-provoking and really makes you dig into the deeper levels of coaching

The 3D Coaching Institute is a very organized program.  The depth, attention to detail, and expertise is profound.  Any coach at any point on there career can help themselves and there program by partaking in the 3D journey.  I highly recommend it.
If you love church groups and touchy-feely lectures, this is your jam. Honestly though,  not very helpful for non-team sports.
Outstanding course
Useful course.
Very good. Very informative.
I could not say enough good things about this course. I honestly think if a coach is not 3D certified, they are probably hurting young people more than they are helping them.
I really appreciate the dedication to this valuable theory of coaching. This is always the way I've aimed to coach, but I've never felt as prepared to do it as I do now.
I thought that this was some short presentation that our AD gave me to review.  Little did I know that it was a whole class that will help me become a better coach, a 3D coach!

3 Dimensional Coaching has a great deal to offer coaches of all experience levels. The course offers a plethora of strategies to engage our athletes, our communities and ourselves in positive ways. The course acknowledges the challenges coaches face and offers them opportunities to grow and engage in a new and constructive manner. Definitely worth the time and effort.
This course allowed me to discover more about myself and the deepest meaning of what I want to accomplish as a coach.
Even though very time consuming, this 3Dimensional course will help to improve not only the beginning coach, but the veteran one as well!
Even though very time consuming, this 3Dimensional course will help to improve a beginning coach, but a veteran one as well!

I absolutely loved the 3D coaching course. It is a lifetime of lessons for coaches that can be explored before the season even begins. I am very grateful for the opportunity to hear the wisdom of these coaches.

Best coaching course I have ever taken, period. Wish I would have taken this course 14 years ago when I started coaching.  I would encourage every single coach and program in America to take this course. I know this will change who I am as a person and a coach and look forward to the impact that will have not only on the many young men in our program, but on my family and friends as well.  Thank you Jeff, Mark and Wes.  And thank you Joe Ehrmann for your amazing influence on the coaching profession.  Well done, guys!
Great ideas and practices. Highly motivational.

This is my 42nd year in high school athletics and my philosophy has partially aligned with the curriculum but it was never packaged. Now as an Athletic Director, I have the capacity to bring in into the entire program. This course came at the perfect time in our society.

column3: ETHS BOYS ASST TRACK TEAM COACH
column7: THIS WAS AWESOME LOVE A LOT OF GREAT TO START USING ON MYSELF AS WELL AS MY ATHLETES AND THE TEAM AS A WHOLE
This training makes your soul feel  inspired to love through sports.

As a physical education teacher I was skeptical about what I had to gain from this course. This course gave me SO much material, changed my thoughts about numerous topics and renewed my drive to be the best teacher I can be, but most importantly provide the highest quality physical education and support program that I can.
Provides a new outlook on impactful coaching!
This program has instilled even more excitement and hope for developing current and future athletes and coaches in my sport program.
Thank you so much for 3D Coaching program.  I have been coaching for over 30 years and I'm very excited to start my new journey in coaching in 3D.  Ready to start year 1 all over again.

Took a break from coaching after a few failures and thought about giving up completely. After taking this course I am more confident than ever to make a success of my coaching journey and make a positive impact in all lives I will be in contact with. Thank you 3D!!!
I enjoyed the resources giving to me to help me be a better coach. They gave lots of examples to help extend yourself better.

I think they have done a great job of outlining the underlying tenets of coaching and mentorship.  This goes beyond the simple act of coaching athletes.  It's about helping build better relationships and increase personal responsibility and action.
This course was outstanding and I highly recommend it.  If you are still a 1 dimensional coach, please stop.  Great course and very helpful with strategies and examples.

This course was fantastic.  Much needed in a time like this with so much uncertainty.  I have been a coach for over 12 years, this would have been my 5th year as a Varsity Head Coach, honestly I am not at the Job that I want.  This helps to fuel my passion for my next job, the people that I work for are taking the passion out of what I was born to do.  This course helped me to realize that I am in the Job that I am supposed to be in at this time.  But, if I ever get an AD who actually "loves" me and cares about me instead of their job and retirement....Look out, I can help young athletes do some Extraordinary things.  Not sure why God is keeping me in my current state.  Or is it me...Lost coach here with NOBODY helping me to grow.  You guys hiring?  If we ever can play again?

I thoroughly enjoyed taking this course. Although I am not a traditional "coach" I have daily interaction with student athletes. I am excited to take what I have learned and implement it into my daily practices as an athletic trainer.

Great course, that has already impacted my life, I really hate that we missed out on our season this year due to Covid-19.  I would love to be able to review this course in July and August right before I see my athletes again.
I wish we had 3D 25 years ago, great course!!!
I recommend this program for every coach in this planet. Words can’t explain the knowledge I have gain from this program. Just try it and your journey as a coach will never be the same.

I love this course. This may the best training I have ever received towards my passion. This is better than any clinic that I have attended and using this framework, I feel like I can coach any team in any sport and e somewhat successful just because of the transformation this framework does for a team and a community. I highly recommend this training for any coach and I would want my entire coaching staff certified in this framework. Thank you for the knowledge and experience.
Lots of good info & strategies to dig into.
I wish I had 3d training 25 years ago. It was extremely beneficial.
An excellent coaches training with practical tools to help reach our athletes and their families.  Very useful

Multiple times I have referred to what I have been learning in these modules as, "pure gold."  Personally, I had never considered coaching before, it wasn't even on my radar.  However, a few years ago I found myself in a new town, in a new school, taking on a new role - as cheer coach of a brand new program. I didn't even know where to begin! The lessons I've learned here will be invaluable to me and to our program that has steadily grown every year.  I can't wait to begin implementing what I've learned in hopes of focusing more on the 2nd and 3rd dimensions and really getting to the hearts of these kids.
Videos helped drive each point.

Every coach needs to take this course as it will challenge him/her to reach beyond what he/she already does to provide student-athletes with the best environment possible to be the best version of themselves possible!

This course is an awesome reminder of who we should be as coaches and why we coach. I strongly recommend this course for coaches of all experience levels and coaching levels. Thank you for having the vision to create and share this with coaches.
Very uplifting.  It makes me reevaluate everything as I am closing out my career.

I had a great journey of learning and all the content was thought out and planned, I could feel in my spirit it was prayerfully prepared, all the words were like a knife(Word of God) piercing one's heart. All the learning and concepts are practical to apply.

I had an amazing time learning and the message was precise like a knife(Words fo God) piercing through my heart. It was very evident and I could feel in my spirit that this was prayerfully built. Very practical at the same time. Thank you very much for this heart changing journey.
Very inspirational.
Great course1
quality format and insight

Sooooo inspiring. The different scenarios got be so excited about going on to the next module. You all have truly hit the nail on the head on how to help and develop our kids to be effective in our community and mainly to themselves. Kudos to each & everyone of you to make this happen. 
Thank you
OK
The course confirmed a number of ideas that I had arrived at in the course of my coaching career. It was very encouraging to hear these ideas articulated.
Very motivating. This definitely makes me think of ways that I can not only be a better coach in terms of win/loss records, but also to help my girls grow as young women.
There is always something to learn! Embrace life long learning.
This course is great for coaches to understand the student-athlete and their family.
This program re-energized me and reminded me why I became a teacher and a coach.  Sports are not just about winning games they are about learning how to winning at life.

This was a very eye opening experience for me.... there is a lot of tools that i will be using in coaching and in my family life. 
Thanks,

I would highly recommend any coach, regardless of how many years experience they might have, to take this course.  It will make you reflect on why you coach and the importance of relating to today's student-athlete.

As a newer coach, I've struggled with ways to connect with and coach my players on the 2nd and 3rd dimensions. This course has given me so much more insight and practical approaches to become a 3D coach and pour into my athletes in a way that encourages, nurtures, and grows their body, mind, and hearts.
Great Course
Great coruse
An excellent, reflective tool for all coaches, regardless of how long they have been in the game.

This course has completely changed my outlook of my role as a coach, the 3D coaching methodology makes me want to be a better person for my family and players on the field.
The transformational purpose makes you reflect on everything you are doing, does your program reflect the right message, do your coaches know their ‘why’. 

I would recommend this course for everyone who is looking to get into coaching or coaches who are looking for a new lease in life, the course would be beneficial for ever level of a coach and really has the capacity to make your philosophy change for the benefit of the players, your family and even the communities your are in.

Absolutely LOVED this course
excellent course have opened my mind in an incredible way
excellent course have opened my mind in an incredible way

This was so professionally done. This course digs deep into what it means to be a coach and how important our job is for impacting future generations. It teaches you to be thoughtful with your words as a coach and intentional with how you approach every situation
I was very impressed with the material and all of the information.
Wow this applies to so much more than just the athletic field.

The course gave a verbal expression  to a number concepts I had arrived at intuitively over my coaching career and presented  a number of ideas that were new to me. It was very helpful to have these principles explained with accompanying references and suggested strategies for implementing them.
Great information to be able to better oneself as a coach.  I would recommend this to any coach out there.

This was a great course it should be given to every new coach rather in youth sports or high school.

Thank you for putting this together.
The class was well done and offered excellent ways to improve as a coach.
A solid overview of coaching with lots of good reminders for veteran coaches.  Lots of good activities to possibly introduce to your program.
Great Program....good review why I coach and how I can provide a better experience for my players
Needs to work better on mobile devices. Get more diverse speakers.

This course reiterated that I'm on the right course of building my legacy.  It has also encouraged me to go deeper with my sphere of influence.  This past season was incredible using some of these same principals; however, we will truly impact more individuals as a result of 3D Coaching.
Very detailed and examines aspect of coaching.  It emphasizes the importance of developing your coaching philosophy, and what the foundation of a coach should be.
This course was absolutely amazing and I encourage all Coaches to take it. # Dimensional Coaching is the ONLY way to go.

The 3D Coaching Certification course is a strategic journey of self-discovery and reflection that enables ALL coaches to re-connect within themselves and be excited about their role in the community and in the lives of young people!
A Holistic perspective on coaching. It goes deeper and gives you practical life applications that makes a coaches journey impactful.

I thought this course was extremely useful in helping me with strategies to coach beyond the 1st and 2nd dimensions.  I'm looking forward to implementing these new strategies next season and I plan to review this very helpful course material as well.

This program helped to validate many of the things that I have done throughout my coaching career. It also reminded me that I can incorporate other ideas to make me an even better coach and individual.

I though the course was very inspiring and educational. I think the gentlemen who speak in the video are truly invested in making each person taking this course a better coach, and that makes for a pleasant experience. The testimonial stories especially make it inspiring, it makes me want to get right out there for practice today. Thank you to everyone involved in making this happen! I really enjoyed the course!
Very informative and helped me a lot.

Lot's of common sense. There are a lot of great things. In my opinion, this focuses greatly on suburban/urban schools and sports. At times it really seemed to lack strategies for rural schools/sports programs.

This course, no matter where you are in your coaching career, will help guide you towards running a program that is best for young people. They need more than x's and o's, or splits, or plays. They need love and compassion. They need to feel like they belong.
love the course, sometimes I had to rewatch a video to get credit and move forward , happened maybe a handful of times

column3: Assistant Athletic Director/Director of Football Operations
column7: I thoroughly enjoyed this course! It has made me look inward to be better outward as a coach, husband, and father.
A great course that I would recommend to all coaches. A very in depth course that teaches a coach how to handle emotions and getting to the hearts of the players and community.
This course helped me gain more knowledge as a coach. I've learned many strategies to help make me become a better coach for my students in the upcoming years.
What an awesome program to help change my perspective on how to approach coaching. Also loved how they tied the bible into it all. Thank you for sharing what you guys have learned.

A great course. Highly recommend to not only coaches but anyone looking to make a life change.  This course provides you with a new outlook and several strategies on approaching students, athletes, and people in general.

I think the 3D Coaching Course is a very important tool for every coach, and every school district.  The course brings to light the 3 dimensions that we actually instruct athletes through.  I have coached for 14 years, and have prided myself in teaching the fundamentals.  Yet, even with my most talented teams, we always came up short.  I will now coach on all 3 levels.  Looking forward to this new adventure!
I learn a lot about myself taking this course. It was very beneficial for me discovering who I am as a person and gave me the tools to improve as a coach on and off the field.

column3: Computer Science Instructor and Golf Coach
column7: 3D Coaching gives you the why and how to be a better teacher, coach, person. After learning the many ways of being a better teacher, they give you many great lesson plans to help you implement what they are teaching.
I enjoyed the entire course. Especially the FCA addons at the end of each module.

Overall I thought the content of this course was very interesting and very helpful. The only problem I had with it was I came across several technological errors. Almost every time I hit submit for a quiz or a short answer response my screen would freeze and and when refreshed all of my responses were lost, which was disappointing especially on my short answer responses. However, I am glad that I had the opportunity to learn these 3D Coaching techniques and look forward to being able to apply what I've learned to my coaching style. I also feel this course will help me out a ton with my future in the sports psychology field.Thanks for sharing!
N/A.
Great course

I felt the course was actually very good and helpful. I absolutely loved the involvement of the FCA and their videos they provided. Faith is a big aspect of my life, to receive helpful knowledge in coaching and adding faith was phenomenal. Thank you.
Great message. Wish this idea could go into the classroom geared around teachers and students.

This course highlights those things that coaches should be doing in their program to build community and leadership in athletics.  Useful strategies are provided but too much time is spent on the philosophy.  It is also geared more toward male coaches and athletes, meaning there are few strategies tailored toward female athletes and psyche.

This course was awesome! It provides a ton of strategies in an easily understandable and accessible manner. I was able to truly understand the power of coaching while completing this course. Thank you!

This course was fantastic through and through. Every single unit was valuable and practical. I now have pages of notes to apply to my coaching and to life in general, and practical plans for how to implement these new ideas. I sincerely hope the course remains available to me for years to come, as I would retake the course each year (even if it was the exact same content) to be "refreshed" and to undoubtedly glean new information from each additional viewing. Thank you for the work you've put into this - I'll most certainly be a better coach/wife/mom/citizen because of it.
This was an incredible course. The things learned doesn't just apply to coaching but also parenting/life. I'm a better person because of this course
I thought it was great. I've been teaching and coaching for 27 years and I learned soooooo much new and exciting information. I can not wait to utilize ALL my new coaching and teaching skills.
this course was great and a lot longer than first thought.
good
pretty good
Great resource...this helped my personal growth in ways I can't explain!

Some of us have been doing this, developing this, and employing this for many years of our coaching careers.
I believe you are on the right track, you have some real credibility and some great insights. I feel that for some of us, God has blessed us and bestowed upon us the great privilege of allowing us to coach and  to peruse our life long endeavor,to work with people in the realm of athletics.
Great course I would recommend it to any coach
Great course I would recommend it to any coach
Very insightful and enlightening!

This course is absolutely life altering.  It changes the way I look at our profession.
Loved this course. Stick out the first few modules because it will change your coaching and give you the resources and strategies to make a difference.
I really enjoyed this.  I believe I am on the road to becoming the coach the Lord wants me to be.  I recommend this course for every coach at all levels.
This is a great course with many things that will be applicable for my future teams.
So powerful, required for any coach!

I took this course as a part of my Art & Science of Coaching course in my Master's program. Of all of the classes in my program, nothing has gotten to the heart of my career choice and my passion for what I am doing like 3D Coaching has. Where most of my coursework leading up to this program felt like tasks to check off and was material that I mostly completed and then did nothing else with, the material from 3D Coaching had me engaged in reflection and I found myself excitedly sharing pieces of the course with my colleagues, sporting community and families. I highly recommend this course for those who want to take their coaching to the next level!
This course was comprehensive and inspirational.
Great program.  It really helped me realize how I need to changed the way I was leading.  Thanks
This course was definitely worth the time it took to take it. I enjoyed it and took a lot of good information from it, and I will apply it to my team and coaching staff.

Eye opener to evaluate what coaching is. There is a place where all coaches can bond and develop in order to develop their own athletes. Learning there's an extrinsic and direct physical benefit to exercises, but also an emotional and intellectual component that comes with coaching. Amazing.

I have been coaching for over 30 years and the last nine at the high school level.  The past couple of years has been trying due to entitlement from both athlete and parents but after taking this course it really has showed me new approaches and the motivation is back. Thank you 3Dimensional  Coaching.

There was a lot of great information in this course.  Some of the videos were a little long and could have been shortened to get to the point, but all in all I feel that this is a great course for coaches to take.
This was a great course for beginning and veteran coaches as well as anyone working with youth.
This was a great course for beginning and veteran coaches as well as anyone working with youth.
Very eye opening.
Awesome, learned a lot of things that I didn't know!

Too long and I keep having to do this for schools with no feed back or follow through

I am very thankful for this course.  This course has opened my eyes to the things I was doing right and the things I needed to change.  I am thankful to have it to go over again and again to implement more season after season.
Thank you
Great way of growing as a coach and person. Really makes you think about how you have been coaching and what you can do to constantly grow.
I enjoyed every module of this course.  It has really made me think about my own team and what I can do to create a stronger community and build more meaningful relationships with my athletes.
Best Course yet!
Essential for any coach.  This course gives many practical tools to meet the body, mind, and hearts of our athletes.

Good experience working through and being reminded of what it means to be a coach.
Easy to follow program that was some of the best information and guidance I have ever received. Awesome! I will use this for a lifetime.
The course was thought provoking and easy to identify with the work we are committed to at our school.
This course is exceptionally inspiring.  It has equipped me with all the knowledge, skills and tools for 3D coaching. It has set me on a path to achieve my transformational purpose.
i love the structure and journey , love the videos and personal stories. the faith based add on is also a great insparation
It was a great resource and requirement to become the best coach I can.
Very thorough and easy to follow.
Excellent course, would recommend to new and experienced coaches.
Amazing course. Extremely helpful in all aspects of coaching and life. Highly recommend.

This course showed me how I can improve in the sport and a person. Continue to build the relationships with the staff, players, and community. The course opened my eyes on things I have already been doing and how to be open minded in the changes for the best.

Loved this course!  3D coaching made me evaluate my coaching and identify the changes I needed to make to become a better coach and person.  I recommend this course to anyone who wants to become a better version of yourself going forward.
This was AMAZING, couldn't stop once i started the course. Always great to get experts confirmation that we on the right track
Very helpful and beneficial as an older coach trying to get through to athletes in this day and age.
It was fantastic and I really learned a lot about the other dimensions of coaching. I know I can take this information and help my athletes be successful in life.

I am very happy my Athletic Director gave the coaches in our district the opportunity to take the 3D Coaching Course! It is a great course! I know I will be more intentional when I am working with my players because of the lessons I learned in this course! Thank you!
It was amazing !!! Thank you !!!

Good course.

This was an informative class. It was definitely worth our time!

great course

Thank You

3D Coaching has opened my eyes to the realm outside of the X's and O's. It provided an excellent framework on how to coach beyond the skills and tactics. This is a must for all coaches and leaders!

I greatly enjoyed the content of this course and the process that I went through from beginning to end.  I feel that this course addresses specific obstacles that I have been trying to overcome.  I have been given easy to follow strategies that will help me overcome these obstacles and become a better mentor and coach.

I enjoyed the course.  I liked that it really made you think about yourself and how you do stuff.  I really liked that it gave examples of how to apply 2nd and 3rd dimensional strategies.  Just having examples like that can give people some great ideas for what they could do.
3D Coaching has set our athletic department on a new course.  It has given all of the coaches and myself new ways to look at how we coach and interact with our student-athletes.

What an amazing course! Fortunately, I have learned many of these techniques in my life, but this course put everything in order very properly and tactfully.

This was very powerful and provided a lot of self reflection. This reminded me to be very intentional in what I do and say to make our department one of servant leaders that want the best for all of our student athletes.
This was a good course. I felt like a gained a lot of new perspectives on how to approach student-athletes.
This was a good course

I took this course to learn how to help my boys with the mental aspect of basketball.  In the end, I learned much more about myself.

This course provided a life changing perspective and insights of today's kids and parents that brought me to see the way I need to make changes in how I connect with my athletes to achieve mutual success and fun for us all.

Great course.  Self paced approach allowed me to feel comfortable moving forward at a pace that fit my busy schedule.  Videos were short and on point.  They really spoke to me as a person.  Awesome stuff

Lots of fine ideas.
Great Advice!

Very informative

This was an amazing course! 3D Coaching allowed me to examine how I can deliberately impact my athletes' lives. I believe I was coaching through only the First Dimension; I have to be mindful of moving to the Third Dimension.

This course really pushed me to think about my role in shaping my athletes' lives. We want and hope to have a positive impact on our their future but don't know how to be honest. The 3D Coaching course gave me a clear, step-by-step playbook on how to spark change in their lives and mine.
It opened my eyes to better ways of being a father a husband a friend and a coach a co worker
Great course, valuable information and will definitely recommend it to other coaches.

Amazing Course. Should be required for all coaches in these days and times. We still have to many Coaches that are old school and don't seem to give the athletes the training and support they deserve and need. There are to many that still care about the win and only the win.

Rule #66 in the benedictine tradition was they placed a "porter" at the gate to see and care for all the sojourners that came their way.  Whether they needed food, water, first aid, a kind word, or whatever, these "porters" did their best to see that each person got what they needed.  I believe this course teaches the same service.  They loved and served their fellow man with everything they had.  May we do the same.
This course offers a comprehensive approach to developing a coaching philosophy that can transform a program, school and community.
Very eye opening strategies that can be implemented in different scenarios
Awesome content and information provided throughout the course.  I was thinking and contemplating how I interact with my athletes from the very beginning until the end.

I really enjoyed this course.  It helped me to think about why I coach and gave me a new outlook into coaching.  I am excited for our next season so that I can apply some of the things that I have learned!

I really enjoyed this course.  It helped me to look into why I coach and gave me a new outlook on coaching!  I am excited to get started on our next season and apply many of the things I learned from this course!
This course is extremely empowering and moving. It makes you dig in, not only as a coach but a human being. By the end of this course it has you wanting to go out and change the world!
ok

Great course, look forward to going through the modules again.

an eye opening course that gives you the keys to unlock the full potential of an athlete. keys not only to open an untapped skill set, but more importantly to unlock an athletes full potential as a person.

good course- could be shortened.

Great course. I learned a lot of ways to incorporate new techniques with old ones.

This course is for the coach who wants to go to the next level and really understand their role in today’s society. This training provides structure that coaches need, no different to what they try to provide athletes. 

Major Jason Tolbert
US Army

The 3 Dimensional Journey has changed the culture of our department. We have seen positive relations among students, coaches, & administration blossom with the implementation of the 3D strategies. I would like to Thank Wes Simmons & the 3D Staff for their wisdom & guidance through this journey to build a championship culture at Ankeny Centennial High School!

Great job with this, I really enjoyed the videos, and this will definitely help in my journey in becoming a better coach and teacher for future student athletes.

This course brings together so many of the key elements of having a successful program, as well as a successful life. I highly recommend the course.

column3: North Polk High School VarsityVolleyball Coach
column7: Very useful and informative presentation and information that challenged me to rethink my coaching.
NA

No information was groundbreaking or hard backed in science. I have read the book as well, it was a gift from our FCA leader. I think you were an amazing coach, and had great impact on your athletes. But I don't think everyone needs to coach this way to leave a positive legacy. I'm not saying the 3 Dimensions of coaching aren't applicable. I use them everyday. In my young, humble opinion,  we don't need to structure them the way you tell us to to be successful. John Wooden for example, had a very different pyramid of success.

This is one of the best online courses that I have ever taken. It's a compliment when I say that it was difficult to not sit down for hours on end and take in all that was gifted to me in this course. The course addressed many current topics while focusing on self-examination. I enjoyed the way the information is supported both spiritually and through research. In more than 20 years of coaching, it's one of the best experiences that I've ever had.

column3: Volleyball Program Head and Varsity Head Coach
column7: Outstanding course that should be taken by all coaches at all levels!

This course opened my eyes to the side of coaching that is ever evolving and has changed drastically in the last decade. Getting to know the student athletes character and shaping them into a citizen who will be successful in life is key to creating a positive athlete on the field/court. This course provides multiple view points and strategies to help coaches understand how to address student athletes.

This course opened my eyes as a coach to many other approaches to getting to know a student athlete as a person and pushing them to their fullest potential. I am confident that many coaches come out of this course having a better understanding of how to address an athlete and their character for their future rather than the play on the field/court.

The 3D Dimensional Coaching Course allowed me to look within myself and make a self evaluation of where I currently sit as a coach and as a parent and gave me the necessary tools to improve in areas where I may fall a little short and gave me the reassurance that I needed in areas where I feel that I may excel in.
Loved this course, very useful for everyday life.
Sachil Perera

I really enjoyed this course. It helped me think about who I am as a person.  Students are so influenced by coaches and teachers.This influence can be negative or positive. This course has helped me remember why I became a teacher to begin with. My sport was diving as a child. My coach was the most encouraging adult I have ever known. Thank you for helping me realize I can be that encouraging to my students. I really enjoyed this course.
Great

3D Coaching is an outstanding resource for coaches of all levels to taking their coaching to the next level.  Any coach would find this course as time well spent in their development in the profession.
Very insightful
Enjoyed journey.  Very manageable and gave me great insight
Excellent and indepth approach to be a transformational coach
There is a lot of great information and input.

This course forced me to really take a step back and evaluate my own coaching practices. I realized that I was doing some of the 2nd and 3rd level coaching without even thinking. Now that it has been brought to the forefront I plan on being more deliberate with how I approach these 2nd and 3rd levels. This program has given me so many valuable ideas that I can't wait to implement with my players and families.

I thought this course was very helpful to see what type of coach I am. I have been coaching for 17 years and after taking this course, I realize that I have become, over time, a 3rd dimensional coach, but it took years for me to accomplish this. I love the additional tools I have picked up to continue to grow as a coach. This is a great course for a new coach and I wish I had it when I first started.

This course does exactly what it says it will:  it forces you to question why you really coach and why you want to be involved in student-athletes' lives.  It truly does create a transformation in your approach.

This is a great program! I love the fact the plays into the whole ecosystem of a person, emphasis is placed on the process.
This course not helps the players but also deals with the heart and emotions of a coach! 
This is awesome!
excellent

I just finished by 3-D  coaches training.  I was skeptical at first about doing this program but after doing it I don't think there is any other clinic or session I have watched that has a greater impact of my ideas who I am and more importantly who I want to become,   I know this program may be required for head coaches to take but if you haven't taken the course it is the best money I have ever spent.
The 3D program made me not only reflect on what kind of coach I was but also what kind of coach I could become.  It reaffirmed some of the ideals that I had but also questioned others.   It also makes made me reflect on what type of coaches I have been influenced by in my growth and journey.

This course teaches you to look beyond the game, and focus on developing your athletes as leaders. These future leaders will learn how to be successful and love because you taught them the framework of how it is done.

The 3D coaching gives multiple examples of how I can use this in my program. Gives plenty of evidence and real-world examples of people that use this. Additionally, the faith based add on gives a connection to what I believe, and how I can bring that in to my coaching.

It has been an amazing learning experience. I have slowly learnt the course over the past 3 months and have regularly applied its training techniques as well as its 2nd and 3rd dimensional strategies and it has change a lot of my athletes lives. 
But i realise now that the last few modules are based on me and who i am. And i have to work and improve this side.

The course was well organized. The presenters appeared to truly believe their message. Improving as a coach or person requires the ability and willingness to learn and to question prior processes. Focusing on all three dimensions is necessary to be a complete and effective coach. The scoreboard is not the only way to measure success.
Superb! learnt a lot. Thank you very much.

This course encourages you to reinvent your coaching style. In the future, I plan to be more intentional when I coach, recognize my growth alongside the athletes' growth, and to always stay true to my own values and goals. Sport is way more than a win-loss record; it's about having fun, challenging yourself, and building lasting relationships.
Is a very insightful course that gives me a brand new perspective of how we as coach should renew our approach in coaching the 21st century athletes and fulfilling the core needs.
This course has inspired me to not only transform as a coach but also as a husband, father and person.

I started this journey as a first dimension coach, now i know i have learnt what needs to be done for a better result/outcome through a long term athlete development using the 2nd and 3rd dimensions which is gonna be a long learning curve but definitely the best learning experience
This course  brings to light and shows you how to use a multi-level approach to coaching and your personal life.

WOW!
 I watched and studied the class in one week Could not stop watching the videos. I know this is about coaching students, but I will become a better AD because of this course. I cant wait until I have a coaches meeting.

Thank you! Thank You!

This course was great for reflecting on my own beliefs and made me think of how I want to help student athletes. The testimonies at the end really show how important coaching in all three dimensions truly is!
I enjoyed how it pushed my thinking of coaching - to more than just the performance in the pool.
Especially like the short answer parts that make you really think about yourself as a coach.
No one can walk away from this course and not be challenged in every way to coach people in who they are, rather than coach skills to players so they can be better at what they do.
An outstanding course.  It provided me with the knowledge, skills, and resources to become a better coach.  I am extremely excited to put what I have learned and planned to work this upcoming season.

Fantastic course, every coach around the world  should invest the time in 3D coaching!  This was truly a transformational journey that will inspire and motivate you to be a better coach, but more importantly a better person!!
This is was a great course
Very Informative

This was a very rich experience in my life. I have coached nearly 40 seasons between volleyball and softball and I wish I could have had this training as a young coach. To meet with other coaches and process the information was valuable. I feel very connected to those coaches now and I know we are there for each other. This training will positively impact our school community. I am very grateful.
I was not a fan.

This was a great opportunity to reflect as an experienced coach. I reflected on some good things we are doing and also some things that need to change. We are all doing some good things in our program but also we are doing some things that we might think are good but are really counter productive.
Well worth the time and effort. 3 Dimensional Coaching is a must if you want to succeed in coaching the 21st century player.

When completing courses like these I always wonder if I am going to learn anything tangible.  Well this course far exceeded my expectations! I highly recommend this course for both new and seasoned coaches!

Comprehensive

Loads of knowledge; not just for beginning coaches. Every coach can take something away from this program. If nothing else, it will reenforce what you have learned over the years about best practices when working with today's youth. 
This applies not just to coaches, but to anyone who works with kids. Kids have changed and we, as adults and mentors to today's youth need to adapt to best serve the kids of today. This program gives you the tools and the knowledge to best prepare yourself and your staff to work with today's student athletes.
This is an amazing and fulfilling course. Full of thoughtful insight and positive ideas. I can’t wait to empower my community with the new tools that have been revealed to me.
Outstanding and Inspiring.
I felt like most of this content was common sense. As an educator the same beliefs are being pushed through already...this isn't a new idea. It's being used in so many other professions already.
This was a very interesting and unique course which challenges you to consider how you view your position as a coach.
Opens your eyes to new ideas that may help connect with players that I struggled to connect with before.

I appreciate the clear teaching and affirmation of sound principles when it comes to coaching. It's more than technique, skill, and drill. It's about love and relationships that transform lives for the future.
This program was very valuable I am encouraging all of my coaches to look into this program.
This was very well done.  I enjoyed all facets of the presentation.  I am going to encourage my coaching staff to look into this program.

It's great! I found techniques that I could immediately implement at my next practice and really made me think about the legacy I would like to leave, not just as a sports coach, but as a PE Teacher as well!

This was an eye opener. It helped me to see a more global picture in the athlete's development. It also lessens the pressure for me to have the athlete perform solely in a physical realm. Great course!
great
Great
A lot of great techniques and practices to reach the hearts of your athletes.
A very strong and helpful course!!!

column3: Head Baseball Coach Salt Fork High School
column7: I enjoyed the chance to reflect on my purpose and goals.  It was an inspiration to find a way to better myself and my coaching.  It was a great way to start my season.
Life changing. This course put words to what I’ve felt in my heart, and has given me a framework to incorporate the desire to lead these young men into adulthood.
NA
Course gives a great framework to live and lead a life that is dedicated to athletics being rightly understood.

The course was well laid out and was easy to follow from module to module.  I feel as our program specifically has already been heading in the right direction as a "3D" program, however, this course has made me think much deeper.  It has forced me back into a growth mindset as I know there is so much more that we can still accomplish as coaches and as a 3-dimensional program.  I look forward to discussing my transformational purpose statement, my notes from the course, and my plan with our staff as we work towards a new season and beyond.
This is a great course to help you grow as a coach, employee, and as a person.
This course helped me understand the concept of the 2nd generation of entitlement.
Great information. I would like more concrete information and less fluff and story telling to shorten the 8 hour course.
Very informative information that will assist you as a coach or teacher to help with life learns.
I thought this course was easy to understand and flowed well as a piece.

This was an amazing training/journey. It brought out emotions and thoughts you not only want as a coach but as person as well. To go thru this as a part of a new coaching staff like I did was awesome you not only grew as an individual but you grew as a coaching staff and got to know each other so all of you will start your journey together. I would take this training every year to continue to learn and grow in all three dimensions.
This course was interesting and helpful.
Loved all information and presentation.

Powerful yet presented in a simple way.  Life changing principles that are easy to understand, complete with a plan to implement.  I highly recommend this for coaches who are serious about positively impacting their players for life.
This was a very eye opening experience. I'm glad I had the opportunity to take this course to better myself as a teacher and coach!
This course if done correctly will make a difference in your athletic department.
Definitely a life changer for anyone who takes this course. Not just for coaches, bt for anyone who truly wants to change and improve themselves as a person.

3D coaching can transform coaches, players, a school and a community.  3D coaching can instill healthy beliefs, mindsets, and character qualities that are missing in society. Once those are instilled, then behaviors change. If people are connected, loved and valued like 3D teaches then life is full of goodness, and a whole lot of love. What a great program 3D is. The ripple effect is HUGE and I am very thankful to have been coached by a 3D coach when I was growing up and to be a 3D coach myself. Thank you for pouring into lives of thousands via this program.

column3: Head Volleyball Coach- Prairie High School
column7: Very eye opening and powerful. I am excited to bring these tools to the court and in the lives of the athletes I coach!
An excellent overview of the 3DimensionalCoaching framework with an emphasis on how to coach the heart and mind. Could relay the same information in a shorter course.
I thought the information give in this course will benefit the way coaches coach from now on and I believe it will benefit themselves, there players and the community that is around them.

Much of what I learned, I already believed but just hadn't consciously put into practice. This course helped provided a framework in which to anchor myself as both a coach, but more importantly as a human being.

column7: This reinforces many of the things I have done for over 40 years. It also adds a few new wrinkles.

Awesome experience with practical applications from youth to high school!

Not only was this course easy to navigate manually, it also made it easy to navigate inside myself to reform my ideas of how to be a good coach. It gave me great tools to use as my journey coaching continues and it helped me find ways to improve myself so I can help improve my athletes.

Not only was the program easy to navigate and understand, it made it easy to navigate within myself and reform my idea of coaching. It helped me understand my personal beliefs when it comes to my coaching and gave me the right tools to improve myself so I can help improve my athletes.

I am a huge fan of this course. It is valuable enough that I have worked with donors to purchase the course for all of my Varsity coaches and hope to expand it as a requirement for all coaches at our school.
