The Videos about the Girls Basketball and Boys Football Team trying season were very moving. It would be easy to coach a team that wins 100% of the time, but I think to test the well of us Coaches sometimes going through a season like that will show us who we really are. It's not always about X's and O's but about getting to know your players and what motivates them; who are they and what concerns and fears they have on and off the field. I feel if you know your player and what they are about will help you on the field as well.

I believe the losing to win module was a very heartfelt part of this course. If people can take this to help their athletes and students to perform their daily life, it will make this a better world. The 2nd and 3rd dimension is so much more valuable than the 1st dimension.
The steps and procedures to develop the important 2nd and 3rd dimensions were the most valuable part for me. I'd recommend this course to other coaches. Great course, for any level.
The fact that we can help our players with much more than just play a sport is so valuable to remember! I found this course inspiring and it has given me a new outlook on coaching!
This course was very helpful on how to relate to athletes today.

I would recommend this course because it focuses on the relationships with athletes versus just teaching them skills. It will help build life-long memories and have a lasting effect. The most valuable thing was to learn different strategies to use throughout the year to model the 2nd and 3rd dimensions of coaching.

I think it is important for many coaches to ask the question on why they are coaching and if it is about the kids first or themselves. The strategies for connecting with kids were valuable. I am glad to see how positive coaching is making a push into athletes today.
I would recommend this tool because it made real world connections. The strategies for the 3rd dimension were the most valuable part.

It was nice to see that many of the strategies I already use as a coach are inline with the 3D coaching philosophy. It encourages me to continue in this way. I recommend this to other coaches, to new or young coaches especially.

This course has given me the opportunity to take a deep look at myself. I have become more intentional about acting like the coach that I want to be. I think this course allows us to view ourselves in the shoes of an athlete. Before this course I was in denial about things happening in our program.

The strategies to implement immediately were the most valuable part of this course to me. I recommend it because it offers insight into an area of coaching that many coaches who grew up playing their sport during a different era probably didn't see modeled.

Overall I really enjoyed the course. I really enjoyed the 2nd dimension talks. I think they provided structure to thoughts I already had. I also really enjoyed the strategies, while I do not believe I will use them all, they definitely widen my scope of thinking.
I think every new coach needs to take this course to help them bond with their kids. It provides new ways to connect with our youth.

I recommend this course to other coaches. We use 'kids aren't the same today' too much. This gets to the heart of what we need to do to change with them. Writing the purpose statement was the most valuable part to me.

I would recommend this course. It relates to the problems that coaches face on a daily basis, and gives the coach strategies to use to combat those problems. The different strategies to use to build the family concept of a team were very valuable.
Great course for coaches. This ought to be required of coaches everywhere. Let coaches in on the real success to coaching young men/women.

This course gave concrete methods coaches can use to increase the 2nd and 3rd dimension in their coaching skills. It motivated me to be a better coach and to evaluate the things I do well and the areas that need improvement.
I recommend it to other coaches because it causes you to reflect on what's truly important in life. The emphasis on the levels 2 and 3 were the most valuable part.
I would definitely recommend this course. Good things to think about. The 3D Coaching strategies/ideas for activities were the most valuable part.

I would recommend this tool because it really opens your eyes as to what you need to focus on as a coach.Learning tat you need to get to the heart of the athlete and care for them as an individual not as a tool to achieve your goals was the most valuable part for me.
This course give great insight on how to be a great coach, how to build relationships and different strategies to use.

I would recommend this course because it breaks down the generational gap many coaches are likely experiencing with the social media generation. We have to reach these kids through another strategy than the past.
I think this course opens the eyes of coaches and helps us to become a better coach. Learning that coaching is about more than just teaching wrestling was the most valuable part to me.

I would recommend this not only to coaches, but parents and any other professionals that work with kids. This is a much needed change in the mindset of what society believes about kids in athletics today.
This course offers a lot of valuable strategies that coaches can implement immediately. The combination of inspirational stories and practical strategies was the most valuable part.

This was by far one of the most reflective experiences I've ever had as a coach. The reflection on my purpose in coaching and how to make the greatest impact on my athletes' lives was the most valuable part. I definitely recommend it.
I see this is a very important way to keep youth involved in sports so they can get the positive messages and build those relationships.

This is something that all coaches can benefit from. The most frustrating thing a coach can deal with are heart issues. This program offers methods for attacking those issues. The 3rd dimension strategies and the 3D coaching certification worksheet were the most valuable part.
This course puts your coaching in perspective and makes you more aware of what you do as a coach. I would recommend it to other coaches.

I highly recommend this course for coaches. I definitely found the diamond among the roughs when it comes to coaching materials. Any coach can say, 'do this and that,' and you'll win guaranteed. However, this course teaches us that when you coach for developing the whole athlete (the spiritual, psychological, and physiological aspects), that's when you truly make a real difference in each of their lives. Learning about what it truly means to coach on the 2nd and 3rd dimension was the most valuable part. Skills that transcend coaching on the 1st dimension, which almost any coach can do. But coaching on the 2nd and 3rd dimension truly takes upstanding character, which we can cultivate and develop to produce other upstanding characters.

I feel validated in some of the things I have been doing for my programs over the years.  I also learned their is more I could probably do, but I'm doing things the right way. I think this should be something every young/entry level position coaches should take.
The most valuable thing I got out of this lesson is how to be a better coach and impact their lives. I recommend this course because it has many valuable lessons and how to become an impactful coach.

Team Cohesion is something that my team has been struggling with, and this helped me out a great deal with what to do for that. I would recommend this course to other coaches because it helps point out the other points of focus needed to be a successful coach.
This course helps guide you to becoming the coach we all want to be.
This course is very informative and can open new doors for all coaches in reaching athletes on a different level. It gave me an understanding and different approach to coaching and mentoring.

This course really made me focus on what matters and get me to think about what I'm doing. So much of this course was great, but I really needed that help to write the purpose statement and the step by step process to get there was very good.
The most valuable part was learning to recognize a kid struggling and being proactive at handling it. I recommend it to coaches because it gives you details in building morale.

I have always felt that the most important aspects of coaching are the impact you can have on the lives of athletes. This reinforced that ideal and expanded my perspective tremendously. Additionally, this course gives tangible tools to implement the ideals. I'm excited to be on this journey. I'm going to recommend it to our club's director of coaching.

I would absolutely recommend this course! I don't feel that it is appropriate for an adult to coach a child unless the well-being of the child is their reason for being there. A coach who goes through this training would have to look at what they're doing, and ask themselves why they were there at all. A clearly delineated understanding of the various levels of coaching, as well as specific definitions that were backed up with research, were the most valuable thing to me. I loved that these weren't just 'common sense' approaches and that they had foundations in research.
This course is very enlightening and offers much value to coaches. Recognizing that we must evolve! We can not continue coaching in the first dimension alone.

I would recommend this course for both new and old coaches that may be wondering how to reach their athletes and to reinforce some of the things they may already be doing. Thinking about funeral topics, and what really matters when it is all said and done and the impact that I could make after a career in teaching and coaching were the most valuable parts of this course.

I recommend this course because it makes you realize the impact you can have on a player's life in one season. It's not always about the wins, but building relationships with my players and making them better people.

I recommend this course because because I know a lot of folks that when they are coaching are only doing it in the 1st dimension, and not really taking anything else into consideration.  Connecting with players and realizing they are people too, and not just a tool to win shouldn't have to be a spoken thing, but with how coaches and parents approach sports today...it needs to be said.

I would certainly recommend the course as the process truly transforms your future direction as a coach. Unlocking character and having (and understanding) the process through the exercise of forecasting my coaching legacy was the most valuable part.

It was valuable learning more about the 2nd and 3rd dimensions of coaching and helping me understand my purpose and the journey better. I would recommend this course to other coaches - much needed information for all coaches in today's teaching environment.

As a coach of 30 years, 3D coaching has helped me to realize where I have failed in capturing the heart of my players and how I can fix it. I realized I have spent more time in the first and second levels and not nearly enough in the 3rd.
The most valuable thing i got out of taking the course was that coaching also happens off the field. I believe any coach or mentor would learn something new by taking this course.

YES, I recommend this course to other coaches. I do believe most of us coaches get bogged down in the Xs and Os and we neglect the human aspect of our players.I really appreciated the Codes of Conduct and the different strategies such as Spot Light and Journaling that I can use to add cohesion to our team.
The whole idea of teaching to the 3rd dimension was the most valuable part. We have always done this, but it gave me more ideas of what I can do to be even more successful.

Many times our coaches get so caught up in the X?s and O?s of the game, they lose the idea that most kids are out for the fun of the game. What 3D coaching does is to take the passion that coaches have and funnel it through a system that not only coaches them to have fun but also to teach character that will stay with athletes throughout their life in whatever fields they go into. It is a fantastic program that I would recommend to any school or athletic department.
This course provided valuable insights to make myself a better person and coach. Great tips on how to improve your coaching, relationships and communication with your players and parents.

column3: Detroit Lions Director of FB Education
column7: The impactful words and messages from each of the presenters.  I found myself stopping the videos to write down the messages exactly the way they were presented.  The material was presented in a way that hit home with me and will be a tremendous resource for me and our coaching staff to help reach our kids in ways they haven't been coached before.  Powerful and impactful!  Any youth/middle school/high school coach truly in coaching for the right reasons would tremendously benefit from this curriculum.  Impact kids in this way and you are bound to be successful despite the won-loss record. I absolutely recommend it and will certainly do so.

This course was extremely informative and helpful when trying to gain an alternative perspective. The most valuable part of it for me was learning how to perceive my relationships with the athletes that I coach.
The tips on coaching the whole athlete and the ideas to coach beyond the foundational skills were the most valuable part of this course.

Yes! I recommend this course to other coaches! There are so many coaches that I have worked with that could use this to better coach not just their athletes but themselves as well. We can always learn something new and useful. It was valuable realizing that I have actually using a bit of the 3D coaching in my coaching all along and just how important it is to coach the whole child not just the athlete.

This course got me to focus on what my goal is as a coach, outside of the sport itself. I recommend it to other coaches because I feel that taking the time to focus on how you live your life and your purpose makes my time as a coach more meaningful.

Learning how to communicate to students in a meaningful way was the most valuable thing I got out of taking this course. I recommend this to coaches because some of us still struggle creating those relationships needed to reach our students at a deeper level.

This course was very impactful. It encourages the coach to appreciate the opportunity they have to positively impact the life of their players and the importance of capturing the heart, using strategies to build meaningful relations.
This course is a great tool to evaluate what you are doing as a coach and how things could be negatively impacting your outcomes and how implement tools for the season.
This course will change your life. It will make you a better husband, father, citizen and last but not least...a better coach.

I absolutely recommend this course to other coaches. Coaching at another level, a level that engages student-athletes with a world outside of athletics. This program motivates coaches to build better, healthy citizens for their life. As a wrestling coach I can see the value of these strategies in ALL sports.

I found that I realized a lot of underlying factors in coaching that you don't normally see without someone pointing them out to you. It really helped me realize some of the things that I do or say and how they may come off to other individuals. I would recommend this course to other coaches.
The three levels of coaching were the most valuable part of this course. I had never thought to classify it like that. It went well for me.

The course opened my eyes to some of things I wasn't doing as far as coaching my youth athletes. It helped me understand how to coach and develop my young athletes for the long term instead of for the short-term. I have already suggested it to my other coaches in our youth program to help them better understand why I do the things that I do when it comes to coaching. I think it would benefit all of us to be on the same page as far as philosophy.

All coaches should experience this course. Among other things, it highlights the relationship aspect of coaching and reveals coaches' deficiencies. The course emphasizes the attributes in the 2nd and 3rd dimensions that most coaches ignore and perhaps classify as intangibles. This course received my highest recommendation on all fronts.

The funeral topics course was a great ending to the entire course.  The course definitely provided a lot of tools that I will use for many future years. This is a well-rounded course that enables coaches to think beyond the 1st dimension.  Great course.  All three speakers were awesome.

I think this course should be a requirement for all aspiring coaches.  It is the foundation of our purpose in helping our youth. Allowed me to look deeper into my coaching purpose.  Now I have some thought when preparing my sessions.  It's just more than just drills.
I am old school coach and this opened my eyes on doing things a different way. The most valuable part to me was talking about how and why to encourage your players.

I recommend this course because it really opens up your eyes and helps you become a better coach and hope that these coaches see that we need to continue to be a better coach and work on our own self-development to be a better coach! It was valuable recognizing there are many aspects of coaching that most coaches chooses not to focus and how it is pleasing to see that there are some great coaches out there because they want to impact athletes and help them go through obstacles and not focus on the wins and losses!
I really enjoyed the journey to the development of my transformational purpose statement. I'd love to see this multiply to athletic programs everywhere.
I'd recommend this course to other coaches. It makes you re-evaluate your purpose as a coach.

The continued re-affirmation of what sport brings to a person as a life lesson. The breakdown of the second dimension and the third dimension has really made a lasting impression on what I am teaching the athletes. I absolutely recommend this to other coaches. It really puts the priorities in perspective. I think the biggest lesson I have learned is the more you reach an athlete in the second and third dimension; the better they perform in the first dimension. Superb.

I would absolutely recommend this course to other coaches. I would love to make it a requirement for mine in every sport that I coach. Putting it all into perspective was the most valuable part. I think that there were a few eye openers even for someone like me who believes in positive coaching. Also understanding now why this generations family structure makes a difference.
It is vital that all coaches understand and apply this material for their athletes success.

I would recommend this course to other coaches. It not only makes you think about the reason why it makes you write it down and forces you to actually plan stuff. Most trainings just give you all the information and don't make you plan stuff out. Writing out the stuff we want people to say at our funeral followed closely by the transformation statement was the most valuable part for me.
The focus on helping/coaching in the 2nd and 3rd Dimensions.  I have been doing that a little without even knowing it. I will coach in all Three Dimensions now.

I think it is a great opportunity for coaches to look at how they work with their teams and players. It confirmed many of the things I have believed in and tried to do over the years. It also gave me new ideas to use.

This course is a GREAT reminder of how we are supposed to teach and coach and the awesome responsibility that we each have as coaches. The reminder that what I do on a daily basis is the most important job in the world. To help my student's / athletes to be the very best that they can be both in sport and in life is critical. Lastly, my job is to love each and every student that I teach / coach.

I felt the most valuable thing I learned that it is much more powerful to the athlete to feel loved, then it is to be rewarded for their success. I feel this course really changes the way we want to reach our kids and stears away from the traditional old-school way of coaching.
I recommend this course because I think it provokes reflection to be a better mentor. I like learning about the different perspectives that coaches had about programs and athletes.

This course has been a soul searching journey for me. Allowing me to develop and build a strong program that shows the hearts of its members. It showed me the importance of coaching the entire athlete, not just the x's and o's.
The strategies have already started to help the athletes that I am working with. The most valuable part was thinking of other ways to reach and teach all athletes.
It gives you a good out look about life itself - the importance of a coach in our athletes life. We sometimes forget that.

It is transformational and allows you to think critically about what coaches you have had growing up and how that influences what you think coaching is. Coaching is more than winning, Coaching is more than fundamentals.
I recommend this course to other coaches. A lot of valuable information and an opportunity for introspect.
I recommend this course to other coaches. It allows you to reflect upon current practices and begin improving as a coach all around.
I recommend this course to other coaches so they too can have positive interactions with their teams. I acquired knowledge to improve my team's morale and joy.

YES! I recommend this course. It allows you to see other strategies used that you can implement into your own coaching. What I am doing is two-dimensional and I have a lot to still learn and grow with.
I absolutely recommend this course. Developing core values and creating a plan to emphasize these in our program was the most valuable part.

Yes I would recommend this course to other coaches because I learned a lot of valuable coaching skills that I wouldn't normally learn. I also had the opportunity to learn from other coaches through the videos, meetings, and other coaches on campus. I'm a dance teacher on campus, so it was really awesome to have the opportunity to learn from other coaches from all sports.
Very good, well organized and informational.

Taking 3D was so inspiring and as the end came I found myself wanting more. The spirit of what I have been doing for 30 years as a wrestling coach has been rekindled in me. I feel this course should be mandatory in every Jr/Sr. High School Program. It has truly changed my life. Thank you.
It is a must for anyone who in a position to impact others, which is really everybody!

This is an outstanding message delivered by knowledgeable and passionate personnel.  For any group truly committed to coaching beyond the scoreboard, 3D Coaching provides an excellent vehicle for the trip.
This course was awesome. It helped me look beyond the X's and O's and helped me look at the relationships.
I enjoyed this course. It gave me a new way to view my athletes. I would like more suggestions for application instead of all the quotes.
This course was very helpful and motivational.  I would recommend all coaches and young people considering coached to take the course.  I really enjoyed all of the speakers.
Great Course

This is exactly what are program needs. We have veteran coaches set in their ways, and ambitious rookies seeking to blaze a trail. We are successful and have done a lot of good for a lot of kids, but we can do so much better. This course will revive the desire in the veteran coach and provide positive direction for the younger coaches. I am very excited to start implementing what I've learned. It's not about x's and o's, it's about people. It's about creating that eager athlete who is inspired and will run through a wall for his team because he finds joy in belonging. That only happens when coaches understand and are willing to work on all three dimensions.
I thought it was very interesting and I learned a lot.
Its great with videos and quizzes to help facilitate learning. I love it that there are suggested strategies that we can implement in our coaching.
3 Dimensional Coaching has changed my life and in turn has positively affected the lives of the athletes that I have coached. All coaches should take the time to become 3D Certified!

column3: Freshman Football Head Coach & Defensive Coordinator
column7: Loved everything and I 100% believe in this philosophy.
Essential knowledge that coaches of all ages should learn and implement.
I have nothing but high praise for the course. Having taken the older version, I like the new flow of the course and the added content.
This was a great learning experience.
qw

Very good, in depth and down to earth information. Video and relationship with quizzes is good. Hoping I have a chance to take part in other 3d coaching programs in the future. Awesome keep up the good work.
Course was great.  Learned a lot
Eye opening course, really makes you think about your every action
A refresher for some, this course is a must for all coaches and caregivers.
Excellent course for coaches!

This course helped me to see beyond teaching athletes the skills they need. I have begun implementing ideas and strategies that I learned during this course with my athletes and I can already see the benefits. They are building better relationships, working together, and enjoying serving others. Thank you to 3D coaching for helping me become a better coach for my athletes.

An excellent course in coaching and life.  I have seen many of these ideas successfully implemented into programs which I have coached, and I plan to implement many more of the ideas in my own teams.  The values of 3D coaching are everything I wish I had experienced my entire athletic career, and I will do my best to give to my athletes and students in the future.

I loved the course and think that any coach, regardless of sport and level could benefit from taking the course. Well worth the time invested and the course presents material relevant to all sports and coaching in a different way. Eye opening and makes you think about how you are currently doing things not only in coaching but in life.  I thought that I was doing things well and this really puts things in perspective that we all have things we can work on! I highly recommend this course for any coach no matter what sport or what level you are coaching at!

This course was very much worth the time it took to complete. I would like all my coaches to go through it as it could be a great tool for younger coaches. It was reassuring that some of the things that I currently do are right in line with the 3D coaching philosophies.
I've been a professional coach for 37 years, but I've learned a lot from the excellent course.

Thank you !
learned
Excellent course and very inspiring. I like the interaction and flow of the course. The progression and build-up is great.
Truly moving and helps me to increase my connections and ability to connect with todays youth.

Due to illness, I am fighting back from,  I had to rush doing the course over two days, but it was interesting 
as I follow the 3D philosophy in my own unique way of creating a everlasting bond between coach and player.  Players I've coached from 12yrs old are now adults married and fathers still having a relationship  connection.  Which is a beautiful feeling in Gods presence.
Very good course all coaches should take it.
The 3D course has taught me many new ideas that I will now implement in my coaching.

I though the course is very helpful especially for those that are not used to coaching girls.  This will help you deal better with girls  teams and less skillful teams.
Excellent course!!!
This course did open my eyes to some things that I do and don't do as a coach. It definitely gave me new ideas on how to approach different scenarios throughout the course of a season.
Very informative and thought provoking . It has challenged me to be more purposeful to coach nit just from the first dimension but all three.
Excellent course! Captured my heart and I could not stop watching!
This was a very helpful and eye opening course that i will carry with me.
Gives a different dimension to the knowledge I have learned in my Professional Football life.
This was an amazing course, that should be required from all Athletic Departments.

This course should be a must for every coach at every level. This should be the main course in any coaching curriculum from high school to college and beyond. I also think it could be geared towards teachers and building a class culture. Best class on coaching ever after 27 years on the job.
I loved it. Very informational and inspirational!
Excellent course that sums up sports in 21 century.

I would like to see examplebof sports that are not the highlight within that culture. Meaning, those sports you show on the video are relative to sports that those players love within their country already. Culture already has breed the heart of the sport!
Overall it was good information. It's not necessarily a lot I haven't ever heard or tried to do, but the language used gives a format to present it to kids and for me to organize
Very informative and enjoyable.
This course has opened my eyes to new ideas and validate some things I believed in.

This is a must for all coaches who want to be better and for there athletes and for a long time in coaching. Every coach should take this course to help reinforce how to help successfully reach the hearts of our player.
This is a must for all coaches who want to be better and for there athletes and for a long time in coaching.
Every coach should take this course to help reinforce how to help successfully reach the hearts of our player.
Great course!
Very good

Excellent, truly transformational,

I wish we had time do it in groups for discussion like in the offseason, conference calls or face to face. Would like the course material at my finger-tips during implementation although I took copious notes.

I really enjoyed the way I could do short videos and work at a pace that fit in our busy schedules.  I think it works well to not have to watch long videos because we are all super busy.  But the points got made and were helpful.
Very Good
This course teaches us what we need to build successful programs in today's day and age!
This programs stands out among others like it in the way it goes deep into the heart of the athlete... but more importantly, into the heart of the coach.

I enjoyed listening to all three guys talk about the 3 deminsions that is needed to develop an atmosphere of enjoyment and team cohesion. Not knowingly, I have used a small piece of these things in my own coaching before taking this course such as stepping into the athletes lives outside of baseball, and the kids have responded exactly the same way this course said it would! I look forward to using more of these strategies and developing relationships with my players that will last a lifetime.
3D Coaching opened my eyes to a new realm of coaching.   A realm where I will also practice to my best.

This course changed my life. For years I have been working in the 2 dimension and didn't know to call it that. I'm always looking to improve as a man, as a dad and as a coach, and this course truly opened my mind. I decided that I want to bring the 3D Coaching philosophy to Israel and to spread the good word. Thank you so much for the hard work that you invested in creating this course and for helping coaches all over the world. we can make this world a better place.

Great Course. I have had the privilege of listening to Jeff in person when he started this journey and it shows that he is always refining his work. Very organized information and a clean digital interface make the course easy to follow.

If you are looking for ways to learn about why Christ has called you into this field, and how you can use your tools to honor Him, then this is the course for you.  It will inspire you, and refocus what it is that your coaching is all about.

The updates are excellent. The course was fantastic the first time and it is simply better. Love the updates on Community, Accountability, the place to put tools in the toolbox and the ability to go through so many resources.
Terrific material!
Makes you reflect on your past as a coach and determine what you want to be in the future.
The course was very helpful in giving ideas on how to work with this generation of students.  They have changed since twenty years ago and it gave me tools to change with them.

An amazing course that has completely changed my perspective and mission as a coach. I am glad that this course, through the hand of God managed to find me, and i am so grateful i am able to be apart of this journey and the next step to come.

Wow!  This course was amazing!  Not only did I learn a great deal about what it takes to be a transformational coach, but it really made me think about my purpose in coaching and the impact I can have on my players on and off the field.

This course was a wonderful experience that had me engaged, thinking, and pondering about my program and how my staff needs to improve our approach.  I would HIGHLY recommend it to anyone who coaches and make it MANDATORY for those new to coaching.

This course has change my outlook and has made me self evaluate my coaching practices.  It made me reflect on something my father who coached for 30 years told me many years ago "If you think you know what you are doing you are going backwards, there is always something to learn."  Completing this course has opened my eyes to new possibilities and things I can do better.
This course was beneficial as I continue to learn to become a better coach. The 3rd Dimension of coaching is one that is imperative to be a transformational coach.

After playing sports my entire life, and coaching for the last 27 years, this course really got me to reflect on my coaches, and the way I coach.  I always knew who I didn't want to model myself after, but this course got me to understand new ways of doing things.  I hope to inspire others to change the way they thing of doing things.
Helped me design a program to support and empower my players effectively.
The course was great, I learned a lot.

column3: Director of Academies at Port Adaelaide FC
column7: 3D coaching course is excellently detailed and delivered so coaches can learn how to lead the 3 dimensions of their athletes lives.
This was such an insightful and impacting course! Thanks you!

I loved it - it formalised many aspects of my coaching that I have been working on for years, and gives me a framework on which to hang an array ideas and philosophies, which I have been wrestling with since I started coaching!

Wow - if you coach, lead or train - and you want to understand how to shape athletes and people as 360 degree performers - then this course is a must - this is an amazing program that looks at how we as leaders can make an impact - that will endure well after the siren sounds and the stands have emptied.
Well done, thought provoking and so practical. It makes you examine yourself and all areas you can improve in. thanks for sharing that with humility!!

I found this 3D coaching course to be extremely inspiring. The content was engaging and compelling right the way thorough, and I am not exaggerating when I say my perspective on sport has shifted as a result of completing this course (positively of course!).

1. Tests well done
2. Videos well done
3. Organized real well

I wish I had this 30 years ago.

God bless

Want to train an African in each country there. How can I help you guys do it?

I have always felt that coaching was always more that just teaching the fundamentals of a certain sport.  With this course it has helped to confirm that coaching is about effecting a student athletes life in ways outside of sport through sport.

This course helps Coaches understand that the changes in our society have made the need for 2nd and 3rd dimension coaching in today's sports arena.  It gives practical strategies to address the issues of the 21st century athlete.  If you want to make a lasting impact on kids, build positive relationships and enjoy the process.

The depth and breadth, the practical, philosophical and spiritual aspects of this course are all excellent, inspiring this tired-at-the-end-of-the-year coach and AD to get excited about next school year.

This coaching course has been catalytic for me in sport and life. As a leadership coach to professional athletes overseas, this course is the perfect blend of transferable frameworks and universal human development issues. Thank you!
-Jordan Valverde
Founder
The Leader's Coach
http://theleaderscoach.us

All coaches should take in this information - whether an old veteran or a brand new coach out of college.  Your kids and parents will be blessed by the use of these tools and techniques.  I believe these ideas and procedures will free up some coaches that are stuck doing the same old thing and keep them from getting burned out.

With over 35+ years in education, coaching basketball at various levels, athletic administration and sports ministry, 3D Coaching has rekindled a fire, put framework and purpose to my current and past work and provided fuel and motive to the future leadership and mentoring I hope to share with those coming behind me in athletics.  Absolutely life changing!  I can't wait to share it with my staff of 30+ coaches as well as any other coaches who has ears to here!  Well done!
Great course, easy to follow, quick and responsive, very useful information and tools.
I have enjoyed the consistent reminders of the laser sharp focus of 3D coaching to deeply impact the culture of sport. It is AWESOME!
Excellent and motivating.  I look forward to putting this to use in my coaching career.
I found this program very insightful and valuable for any level of coaching. I wish I had this during my earlier coaching years.
This was a excellent course for all coaches.  No matter what you coach, everyone should take this. I recommend anyone who is in coaching do this program.

There are a multitude of positive coaching program available for coaches to use to become an athlete-centered coach. 3D Coaching is the best program I have seen. The step-by-step method to develop the transformation statement builds a foundation upon which the 3D framework can be built. The program thoroughly educates on the philosophy of 3D and provides opportunities to apply the philosophy.  The presenters bring a passion and enthusiasm that is not only enjoyable but contagious.
Inspiring and encouraging.  Very practical!
Great relevant and cutting edge material.  Life changing if you will allow it to sink in your heart.
Clear, concise and room to let the person taking the course grow.  This course could change the coaching cultural landscape of our country.

I had been exploring various programs like this one to present to our coaches. I found a couple I liked but never felt 100% committed to making it happen for our coaches until this one. This program is an exciting framework for our coaches that I have no doubt will pay huge dividends for our number one constituency - our kids!
This was a wonderful course that will have great impact my coaching. I will recommend that all my coaches take this course. So we can work together to create culture and community with our team.
Amazing! This course is everything I had hoped for AND more. I'm excited and prepared to begin coaching my athletes 3 dimensionally.
I learned so much from this course and cannot wait to incorporate this into my coaching!
I really enjoyed this course, and will be using the material immediately to improve my coaching ability!
This course gave me the tools needed to improve not only as a coach but as a person.  It made me rethink my approach to coaching and what was really important.
Great Course!
Excellent course for the development of new strategies within the coaching world
I really enjoyed the material of this course.  It's wholesome and genuine.  This isn't something you buy into, it's a blueprint on how to live.
I thought it was excellent.
Excellent and worth the pursuit

As a coach of 30+ years you continue to seeks ways to improve yourself.  The 3D coaching class was by far the best thing any coach can do for professional development.  Many of us started coaching because we loved the game but finding that love for our athletes, community and really our self will solidify the true passion of why I coach.

I loved the content and organization of the course.  As a Christian coach looking for ways to incorporate and improve Godly principles in my job, this course provided many practical ways to use sports to deliver the gospel.  Our overall purpose as coaches is made very clear through great lessons and discussion.
This was a very good course and showed me the areas that I could improve in order to become a better coach.
This course was very informative and helpful
Great!
Excellent
An outstanding look at the lessons needed to show coaches what they got into coaching for in the first place, and then how to actually implement them in their own coaching and teaching strategies.
Great Stuff!
I found this course very helpful I especially like at the end of each module the different stories.  I am gong to use some of the tools I have learned next season.
3Dimensional Coaching has changed the way I see the program, our athletes, and myself. It is an essential framework with which every coach should build their program.
With an open mind this course could change you and your athletes for the better.

As FCA staff this course has equipped me in so many ways as I  minister to coaches and athletes. I could have never imagined how much tools I would be given going through this training . I would suggest all staff go through it so we can be so much better equipped in our high calling to change to world of sport for God's glory.
This course helped me look at coaching from a different perspective and provided concrete methods for how to teach character building part of coaching.

Absolutely amazing information, motivation, wisdom, and so much more. This framework is what I have been subconsciously seeking. I truly believe this is the Lords avenue to save our youth. It was well worth the cost in terms of; value, provided resources, information, planning tools, and the deep thought processes that are evoked. Very thankful for this framework, it is a true blessing in a time of great need!
Glad I took the course, great self evaluation took place.  I wished I would have known about this earlier.
The journey through the 3d program was very helpful. It gave me lots of insight and ideas for the future.
I'm excited to coach using the 3D coaching framework this upcoming season.  This course has helped me focus on why I really coach and what can happen with my influence.

column3: South Coastal Fellowship of Christian Athletes
column7: This is simply the best platform out there for leaders of any type, but especially for coaches.
An outstanding course, both an affirmation and revelation. I feel refreshed and uplifted--reborn as a coach.

This was great!!  I have been out of coaching at the HS level for several years and had stopped coaching and pursued nursing as a career.  I love nursing and was able to come back to the school district as a teacher at the HS level Health Science Academy and now start coaching volleyball again.  I already knew it wouldn't be the same this time.  I have had terrible coaching and some good, and my kids had been getting the bad side of the spectrum.  I knew things would have to changed and felt fairly well-equipped to come in and affect change, but the timing of this training was impeccable!  It gives me the motivation to do it, and the actual tangible ideas to begin.  Again, it was amazing and thank you so much!
This is an excellent course for all coaches to take because this course is all about helping kids be successful in life. This is the way ALL coaches should coach at every level and any sport.
Though I have incorporated many principles, the structure brings the fullness and fills in the gaps of the parts I was missing as a coach.

The 3 Dimensional Coaching course provided an opportunity to address the ever changing challenges facing our kids. I truly believe in my heart it takes a village to raise a child and the strategies and ideas presented throughout this course will help me become more efficient at purposefully playing an integral role in the lives of our student-athletes.
Good course.
Great course!
Great program, very insightful.
Great way to think about important aspects of our lives and how they effect others.
Great.  All Coach and people of influence of today's youth needs this course!!!
A very good course that has a great deal to teach coaches. I really like how it was presented.

I thoroughly enjoyed 3Dimensional Coaching. This course was organized, thought-provoking, and life changing.  I now believe I am better equipped to coach my players at a deeper level than I ever thought was possible.
I have coached for 20 years, and I learned a lot about myself and more importantly,  I have a clear view of my purpose as a coach!

I took the original 3D Course through FCA but found this one to be so much better.  It was more in depth and provided so much more useful information and examples.  The separation between secular and Faith Based offers a greater opportunity to reach more coaches where they are at.  I recommend this course almost daily to coaches I come in contact with.

I believe every coach should complete this course to not only to understand their "WHY", but truly understand how to get to the heart of a student-athlete.  This is my second opportunity to take the course and I was able to reflect deeper by really looking at how I coach and what areas I must still continue to grow.  Each module is a "part" of a whole process that takes you on a journey and builds up to the complete transformation.  The videos allow you to feel as if you are part of the conversation and the instructors are talking directly to you.  As a result I have transformed my way of coaching to another level.  Every coach must explore this journey and jump in both feet.

3D coaching has helped me to organize and better understand many of the thoughts and ideas that have been floating about in my head as I have coached over the last 20 years. This should help me to communicate more clearly my motivations and expectations to student/athletes and their parents.
I suggest this for first time coaches or people forced to coach who have no clue or who aren't aware or mature.
Recommended for young coaches or people thrust into coaching. People so unaware of themselves and others that this helps a lot should not be coaching without supervision.
I really loved the course.  I would like to see more of the strategies in practice.  Not just the coach explaining them.
I loved the course and can't wait to implement some of these strategies.
Its a Such Useful Tool It has already change my coaching pattern
Outstanding great for all coaches no matter how long you have been coaching
I enjoyed taking part and riding the journey...this course has helped me understand my why and regain the joy in why I do what I do...Teach and Coach!

column3: Head boys basketball coach, Jackson HS
column7: Not only is this program transformative as a coach but it will transform your life as person. It's an awakening experience for those leaders who dare to be different.
A life Changing, Athlete Transforming , community impacting, World Changing course.
If someone loves coaching and young people and wants to use the power of their influence to make eternity changes in their players lives, 3D Coaching is for them.
Outstanding!

I took the faith version of the 3D course last summer and thought it was great but this year's updated version with new videos and other features amazed me. I can't wait to use what I've learned. Thanks for what you do!
Great learning format
I really enjoyed this course. I feel as though I was able to pull away at least one valid point that was discussed in each section.
Easy to follow, good information, beneficial for coaches.
Very good course, very informative.
It goes along with the Leader in Me principles, which fits for our school district.
After reading 3D coach, this course was the perfect supplement to take the content of the book to the next level.  To steal from the course, it was nothing short of transformational.

Entering my 37th season as a head coach.  Best course I have taken! Although always wanting to be a 3 dimensional coach, I failed in many ways.  This course not only reminded me of what coaching meant to me, but gave me many avenues to improve.  Every segment was engaging and will help do what is right for our athletes.
Very comprehensive content. Never seen anything this complete in a coaching curriculum.

This course inspired me to pursue coaching in the future. It provided an amazing vision of the impact that a 3D coach can have, and it equipped me to say that I can confidently follow through with it.
I had been debating whether or not I wanted to be a coach, but this course inspired me to coach basketball because it showed how a coach can positively impact kids, and it equipped me to do so.
It has good information but felt a little too preachy at times.

Even though I have coached for several years, this course provided me with a refreshing of the heart to coach from the heart.  I appreciate the strategies provided in this course to help me deal with the current coaching climate.

A good course that covered many important topics of great value to Coaches. Treating others as we ourselves want to be treated is so important. The value of using these tools through sports can add so much to the real reason and the enjoyment that we can experience in sports.
Course was great! A definite eye opener and reminder!
This course is educational and engaging.
This is an excellent course that when taken will lead you to coach with encouragement, support, and love, instead of coaching with fear tactics.  It is a must for the 21 century coach.

3D Coaching has helped me to consistently question every move I make to ensure it is the right move for the student-athlete's and team's growth and development. It was well done and I'm glad my district helped bring this to me as both a coach and an educator.

Want to make a real and lasting difference in the lives of your players, something they will take with them beyond the court or field? This resource will help lay or build on the foundation to positively impact lives in their homes, at their work, and in their communities. Here's to securing the most important victories of all, in the hearts and lives of your players!

It was a wonderful transformational journey as I have come up with transformational statement for my life to transform the lives and communities through the influence of 3 Dimensional coaching I have received and now I want to pour out in to others with what I have been immensely blessed. Great work!! God bless all the hard work and bless many with the resources.
I thought this was a great course and I hope I can refer back to it if needed!

I really enjoyed the course. It was a little long, took longer than I thought to finish. But well put together, great examples for us to learn from. Great teachers and the information is invaluable. It is going to be hard at first to implement and find those mentors and people i can help,  but with determination we can get it done.
Wonderful course! Learned things that are useful for athletes and students!

This course will positively impact you as a coach and as a person. I want to get other coaches in my community certified because it teaches you how to have an impact on your athletes well beyond the field, court, and/or diamond. You will not regret taking this course!
This course has really given me the why for coaching and shows how much of a positive impact I can have on my athletes.

The course was well structured, clearly presented and very motivational.  I personally was challenged and encouraged at the same time. While following the course I drew up a blueprint for a holistic transformation programme for schools & started a fit-teens programme with troubled kids. 
Thank you for the opportunity!

There is no other "product" like 3D Coaching out there to help coaches diagnose the problems and give them the tools and motivation to coach in an honorable way and to see sports be what it was intended to be.

After following this 3D coaching course working in the national level for past 16 years, I truly have gained lot of theory & practical information where I can look forward to take my team to a next level of coaching in the future.Personally you have changed my inner feelings towards the athlete. 
I want to thank Dr. Jeff Duke, Mark Hull, Wes Simmons and other individuals who has worked hard to put this in order.
Great tool for coaches.
Great course for new and experienced coaches.
This product walks you through a process of reflection and motivation toward your goals of becoming a 3D coach and helping your athletes achieve success.
It was awesome

I thought the course material was excellent.  It helped me think of ways to incorporate something that I always wanted to add on to my coaching.  I knew it was missing but I didn't know what it was.  The 2D and 3D tools recommendations are great and as mentioned it is just a framework for coaches.  This framework can be customized to our own specific scenarios.
I thought this was a great course for a coach at any level!

This course has been by far the best coaching course I have participated in.  When we talk about life altering events, I would have to say that this is one. I honestly believed that I had this coaching thing down. This course humbled me making me want to go back 25 years and start over. Although I can't do that, I can start my transformation today!  Thank you.

I give this course a 5 star as it helped open my mind up so much more and realize how many coaches out there are missing out on developing the 3 Dimensional framework. I am excited to organize all of my notes and look back on a few videos.
I would recommend this course to any and all ages as its not to early or to late to start changing your views toward coaching.
Great course with good in its purpose

Covered a lot of territory and turned over many stones that I had not pursued turning over in the past. A great class to take that forces you to think and get involved in what you are going to do to make changes. Very helpful and created a tremendous amount of ideas for the future.
I have been looking for a course, framework like this for 20 years, if you coach a player that is 6 years old or a player at the professional level you this is a course you should look into

I thoroughly enjoyed this course.  It helped me step back and think about things happening in my personal life and my coaching career.  I liked being able to take the time to complete the course and really set goals.  My new purpose as a coach has greatly changed.  My view on life has changed.  This course changed me forever and I am grateful for that.
Great Course I will be having all my coaches take this course once my club team and facility is up and running:-)
It is a wonderful course，I learning a lot coach tool and methods。I will use these methods to in my work。

This course is filled with practical wisdom, knowledge, and strategies for developing a coaching style that reaches into the heart and purpose of coaching and competition. It challenges you to take a look inside yourself ; and to not take lightly, the awesome power and responsibility that you have as a coach to speak life into others around you.

I had read 3D coaching before ever knowing about the training course.  This has been one of the greatest investments in my life.  I have always tried to coach the person over the player, but this course has me intentionally thinking about how I parent, how I teach and how I coach.  3D coaching is a must for anyone who influences the lives of youth in any aspect.

column3: Director of Athletics and Character Development
column7: Coaching in 3 Dimensions is a powerful paradigm shift ... it will "Make a Difference"!
In just a few days this course has already impacted the way I approach our athletes and the way I am going to coach them.
This course helps you to not just look at your coaching philosophy, but how you are able to change the lives of your athletes
This program doesn't just talk about coaching philosophy, but how you can develop athletes that will change their world.
Excellent course!

I have taken this course before in the Spring of 2016 and it was very good then.  This time around, I took it to help facilitate 8 other coaches who took it for the 1st time.  The revamped course is even better that it used to be.  It has helped to changed the lives of those 8 coaches and it will soon change the lives of those they influence and coach.  God bless!

I believe this course showcased some great things I do really well as well as open my eyes to more opportunities I can learn and grow in. It's nice to see how much our youth and young adult athletes are cared for and that it is something great coaches are trying to encourage more.

I appreciate this course and how much it expresses how we as coaches need to love and care for our players just as much as we love and care for the sport itself. It points out a lot of things that we may all already do well, but also helps us continue to learn and grow.
This course is dynamic, informative and cutting edge. In 35 years of coaching this course has been the most insightful of any I have ever taken.
As a brand new coach, I found this course extremely insightful. It gave me a greater understanding  into what it means to be a coach.
Great course
This is a great course for any coach who's trying to find some small edge over others. We're all good at the x's and o's, but can you be excellent in the mental and spiritual levels as well?
I enjoyed the course and every module gave me more tools for how to better myself as a coach and teacher.

This is the best coaching course out there. This truly helps you see the purpose in coaching. It has completely changed how I think, and how I work with my athletes. I would recommend that anyone who coaches take this course.
This was a great course that has definitely made me a better coach.

Phenomenal. This course made me reconsider everything I do, and really helped me refocus on my WHY. It brought into perspective things I was feeling, but didn't know how to express and use. I would highly recommend this to all coaches!

This course gave me even more motivation to push through the difficult times as a coach because in the end it will be worth it. I loved this course because it gave me practical tools and activities to use to be a 3d coach. I also love the faith-based books 3d coaching by Dr. Duke. I think it is absolutely amazing that there is a framework like this out there for coaches and I fully, whole-heartedly believe in this framework.
I think that this was an amazing course! I learned so much and will take many things back to my team.

3 Dimensional Coaching is a must for every coach, at every level.  It is a challenge to push out from our comfort zone as coaches and the 1st dimensional coaching of skill and performance to a deeper, healthier, more intentional method of coaching to the heart of our athletes.  It is a God's hands extended approach that reaps blessings of love, value and purpose into the hearts of our athletes.
Eye opening
eyes opening
This course was extremely beneficial. Helped me to be objective in my thinking.

I really liked this course. I wish that i would have finished it all when I first started the course. One benefit of stopping, right before the end, was to review the course, and take a second look at my notes from when I first started. My wife reviewed my answers on the 3D Coaching Certification Worksheet and wondered who "helped" me to write out the answers, specifically the Funeral Topics section. It was all me, with help from the 3D Coaching course.
I enjoyed this course.

This course allowed me to become a better coach by providing simple step by step strategies.  I have been able to instantly apply what I have learned in order to help me build my program. Very informative, rewarding, and fun!
All in all, an excellent course and easy to follow along.
Good course.
very helpful for high school or college coaches.
Great course on coaching more than the skills!
Very inspirational and educational program. I would recommend anyone that intends to coach young people to take this course.
Lessons directly applicable to my current season, and a foundation to put into the off-season moving forward.

I really enjoyed this course.  We actually used it as applied to a business and it related fantastically.  It gave me confidence to continue in some of the things I had already been doing and provided insight and strategies in areas that were new.  I never could have written a meaningful purpose statement without first taking this course!!
Was a great coarse for not only coaching, but life in general.

This course was GREAT!!! it really helped me learn more about myself and what areas I need to focus on in order to be the best coach I can be!  I have learned so much about myself and what I can do better in my coaching, and as a husband.

We decided to try this course for our business and the results have been very positive. Truly looking forward to our journey going forward. Thank you guys! Well done and God Bless you all!! Roger Anderson Express Electric Inc.
This course is amazing!
This course taught me a lot about dealing with different types of athletes.
Life changing experience! I not only apply 3D coaching to sports, but also to my work, and my home life with my wife and children.

Fantastic.  Highly recommend.  Every HS and MS coach in the nation should be required to complete this course by their state association, athletic director, principal, or board of education.  Even when not required or mandated, every coach should complete this training.

I had taken a 3D Seminar, and was so motivated that I felt getting certified was an important next step to help me become a better coach. The tools I learned in this course are going to help me on and off the field, and help make the athletic journey of my athletes as positive and rewarding as possible. I have already recommended this to every coach in my organization. Well done!
This course was fantastic! I highly recommend it to all teachers/coaches!

This course has fundamentally changed the way I think of my relationship with my athletes as a coach, and my students as a teacher. It has provided me with key strategies to strengthen my coaching in all 3 dimensions. I recommend this course to every coach, especially all those new to coaching trying to find their way.

This course was very informational.  It really makes you stop and think about how much of an impact you have on student-athletes over the course of your career.  We must coach in all 3 dimensions to fully try and reach each athlete.
This course was incredibly helpful and inspiring. It pushed me to better myself for my volleyball program, my players, my family, and, most importantly, myself. Highly, highy recommended!

This was a great course and it has really help me to evaluate how and why I coach.  I have been coaching for 25 years and it was very refreshing to see things that I need to improve on as example, motivator and coach.  I will definitely get my coaches involved with this program.
This was a great course, highly recommend it for anyone entering the field of coaching.
This course was absolutely great!! I learned so much from each of the modules!! Highly recommend this program to any and all coaches!!
Excellent course that explains the importance of focusing on the 2nd and 3rd dimensions of coaching and how to develop those coaching skills.
Great Course! Very Enlightening!
This was a great course. Without a doubt this will improve any coaches abilities.
I enjoyed this course. I plan to use these techniques in my coaching career.
Amazing course that taught me the true importance of being a coach!
Great course! Awesome to have the online course and an in class meeting with Mr. Simmons @ Northwest Missouri State

The online portion of this course was amazing! I learned a ton and I think all coaches should go through this training. It gives the perspective I think so many coaches lack in their daily coaching and interactions with players.
Great course.  My certificate was lost, may I get another, please.
It was a great course.  I will use alot of the techniques I gained.
I found most of this course applicable and helpful.  It was good to do as a group and meet about weekly.
Online material was extremely helpful.
This course is amazing!!!  I highly recommend it to any coach who wants to get more than just the X's and O's of their sport!
Best thing to learn ways how to improve to be a coach and becoming one as well.
It was a thought challenging and an uplifting course. No doubt it was and will be  helpful in my journey as a coach and every day Individual.
It was a very good that taught me a lot about myself and about how to be a better coach.

This course has been absolutely awesome.  It goes beyond the fundamentals, which is what most coaches only try to teach.  I wish I would've been taught these concepts when I was an athlete, but I am encouraged that I can pass this knowledge on to my athletes in order for them to have the best experience possible.

I absolutely loved this course. This will not only help coaches, but can help change a person's transcendent purpose of life and how we are supposed to interact and have relation with one another as individuals.
This was a very interesting and helpful course. Tons of information that will change the style of coach you are or wanted to become for the better.
I really enjoyed this class. A different way of thinking that i have not been exposed to.
Anyone who is engaged in the life of youth and/or athletes must go through this course.  It is indeed transformational.
Great Course. Couldn't recommend it enough. Gives insight & helps you explore key concepts in your own coaching journey. Everything is practical.

column3: Master of Physical Education and Coaching  at The University of Arkansas at MonticelloMethodologies
column7: I really love this program

I absolutely love the content being video driven with task oriented quizzes between.  ensured I paid attention.  Don't why I took so long to get to this course but will review it as often as possible.

Outstanding presentation of valuable course material. As a military leader and long time youth, high school, and college coach, the information learned from this course will be useful in a number of realms.

column3: Head Track Coach; Speed and Agility Coordinator
column7: Excellent Course!  This is a Course that is much needed if you want to fulfill your passion as a coach!

I thought this course was one of the best coaching resources that I have ever seen. I have seen many ways that I can improve as a coach. Even after 41 years as a coach there are many of the strategies mentioned in the course that I will apply next season.
Outstanding course.  Has enabled me to change and grow as coach.
Holy cow!  A changed life is special, but a changed heart is eternal!

Are you looking to improve your coaching skills and expertise?  I highly recommended checking this course out.  I enrolled in this course through one of my masters' classes and couldn't be happier.  The 3D coaching framework is top of the line!  It is clearly one of the best coaching resources I've ever been a part of.  I have learned a diverse range of skills and strategies that I will be implementing for future success.  Thanks for challenging me along my journey of becoming a 3D coach.  ***** 5 Stars NO DOUBT

This course really helped me think about myself as a coach and leader of young people. All coaches think about coaching in the 3rd dimension until it is game week and you have a lot of work to do to prepare for an opponent. This course helps you stay focused on what you know will really help your program be successful. This course helps a coach map out what to do and when to do it so it becomes part of your normal routine every week.

The course was lengthy, but it did help me think of coaching the whole student rather than just the physical side. It gave some good ideas of what to try with students to encourage them and make them better people.

column3: Fellowship of Christian Athetes at Liberty University
column7: Whether a brand new coach, or a coach with years of experience, this course will inspire and motivate you to re-evaluate the whys and ways we coach, refining our purpose and practical strategies in the process.

This course has allowed to me to view coaching in, in sum, three different ways. Through coaching fundamentals, the mind, and the heart, athletes will not only be great at their skills but will be empowered to be great youth that will be become empowered adults.
The coaching coach I've been looking for.
This makes me want to call my girls up today and get started. Its an excellent course for really digging into the purpose of why I do what I do.

As I begin the final decade of my career as a teacher-coach, I look back over more than 36 years of working with players and parents and I can only wish that I had discovered 3Dimensional Coaching as a much younger man.  Now, with the being said, as I begin my 19th year as a high  school athletic director, I am more so grateful to have accessed this valuable resource today, so that I can realize my transformational purpose of helping my coaching staff to lead their players.
I enjoyed it!
Every Coach should have a basic Idea of 3 Dimensional Coaching if he wants to make a positive impact in the lives of young athletes.

This course is truly amazing. I am 23 years old and I have been coaching for 4 years now. God has given me the gift of coaching and I have naturally implied these principles. But this course has grown my horizon and outlook on certain situations. I am the head coach at a high school and run a sports leadership program with my father, all of our coaches will be taking this course before becoming a coach for us!

column3: FCA Area Representative: FCA Baseball Dayton
column7: I thoroughly enjoyed all of the material that was offered. I will be using this to mentor other coaches in my walk!

Most of the courses I have taken or materials I have read related to coaching relate to the first demension of coaching. I appreciated the opportunity to take a course that does a good of focusing on the important demensions in coaching I missed in my previous study. I look forward to seeing how players I coach will respond to this framework.

This course opened my eyes to what more I can be doing in the lives of athletes.  It really focuses your attention on the athlete as a whole person (body, soul, and spirit), and shows to me as a coach all the possibilities I have to positively impact the athletes.
The 3 Dimensional Coaching course provides every coach with an opportunity to reflect on his or her practice while also inspiring coaches to focus on the most important, human aspects of coaching.

column3: Floyd Central Boys Soccer Assistant Coach
column7:
This was a very professional and well thought through course.

Was great to hear from multiple subject matter experts.

I gained a lot of tools and inspiration. 

This has been a Godsend to me!
Outstanding course.  It has changed my coaching methodologies and made me a more positive coach.   Wish every coach in our school would take it.
This was more than a class this was a journey into my soul.  I reflected upon my past and am now excited about my future.

This course has transformed me as a husband, father, teacher, and coach. I had been a 3D coach but did not have the tools or information to be the best I could be. This course provided me with extraordinary depth.

I am inspired and motivated to really make my teaching and coaching go deeper than the first dimension. I feel very equipped to enact strategies to make a deeper impact in the lives of my students and players. This course is rock-solid and helpful for anyone who really wants to invest time into improving their coaching.

Having coached for 39 years and having raised four children, two of whom are coaches, and now serving as an FCA representative contacting coaches throughout south central Iowa, I have found this course more than just an exercise in the techniques of coaching. This has been an inspiration that can affect every area  of my life. I will write a purpose statement for being a father, a grandfather, a husband, a church member, and a community member. I hope to pass this inspiration on to not only my children but on to every coach that God allows me to influence.
This course hit my heart and head at the right spot.  It has inspired me to refocus my purpose for coaching.
I was very impressed. Loved the content. Motivating.
This course should be mandatory for every coach at every level of sports. If this course doesn't get you to look deep inside and assess the way you are currently coaching, then nothing will.

column3: Head Football Coach - Hilldale High School
column7: I started this course looking for a change in my coaching style.  After many years of success I had become burned out and questioning why I am doing this anyway.  Days were becoming tough and I begin to think I need to get out of this profession.  3D Coaching has brought me back to see Why I coach.  It has caused me to focus on relationships and not wins and losses.  This past spring I yelled less and spent more time with my arm around a kid asking how he was doing.  It is not perfect and there are still rough days but I have a new found purpose in my coaching.

This course has caused me to view my role as a coach in an entirely new light. Wins and losses are not the most important thing in coaching, but developing young people to fulfill their life's purpose is so important. I hope to continue this journey as a 3 dimensional coach for the remainder of my career.

Excellent course, if you coach with these tactics you will have a successful season every year. Not by wins and losses, but by the way your team performs and the attitudes they have throughout the season.

This course opened my eyes to the power and influence I have as a coach. I have a renewed desire to make each season count for eternity.

column7: I've had a feeling for many years that we have sacrificed character development for winning at all costs. I'm a big sports fan for all sports(Steeler blood in my veins) and especially tennis. I had the honor of hitting with Rod Laver over 25 yrs ago, a great Grand Slam champion, and a true sportsman/gentleman. Roger Federer and Serena Williams are great current tennis role models, but there have been several in the past that have missed the mark. Thanks for this ongoing course and journey many coaches need to take!

Since becoming a coach at the age of 18, I've always known that my biggest weaknesses goes beyond teaching the fundamentals, the techniques, the movements of wrestling. I struggled year after year to find a way to fill the gaps in my coaching philosophies and practices. I'd had seasons when we nearly came out with top finishes for our program, and I'd had seasons when we nearly bottomed out. I always walked away with that bad taste in my mouth, that taste that would keep me up late at night questioning myself. Had I done the right things? Was I the right coach for this job? Was it time to step away and hand the reins to someone more able-bodied? Yet year after year, I received enough affirmations from parents and former wrestlers that I kept going. Through a series of difficulties and doubting moments, I happened to end up taking the 3 Dimension Coaching Course. I'm proud to say that much of WHAT I believed has been affirmed through the course, but even more so, I now have a much clearer idea and vision of HOW I can help my athletes. Thank you, from the bottom of my heart, for this incredible course.
I think this course would benefit every coach who works with kids, regardless of age, gender, or sport.

this is an awesome course it fit into my way of thinking and how I coach my young Men and women it not all about sport its about life and how we deal with failures and how we succeed in life

It is absolutely amazing course! A thing of a genius of this philosophy and approach is the wholeness. Probably coaches have heard about the individual components that this course speaks about, but the very strong point of it is that you see it in its wholeness as a system in which everything fits in. I would use a metaphor: The individual components that this course speaks about are like individual parts of a human body (arm, leg, head, etc.). I think coaches have read or heard about them and thus they know them. But after this course the coaches will not see just the parts of the body, they will see the whole body. And thus they will understand why the body has its parts, what is their function, so they will know how to use them. So the coach will become a Coach. Thank you very much for the opportunity to go through this course! Martin Kafka, a rugby coach

Very informative and eye opening.

This is a must for every coach. You are too busy not to take this training. Carve out the time and make this investment into your self and your Athelets.
This has made me understand that it is not all about winning or losing, but the lifelong impression you leave on a young athlete.
This course will provide not only the impetus for change and improvement in your coaching, but the tools to bring it about. Be ready to take notes.
I enjoyed taking it and I actually learned a lot that I can implement.

Faith-based integration made the course a two-fold success.
As both a coach and a team-chaplain, seeing and hearing the connections between on-field and off-field transformational concepts was extremely valuable.
There is absolutely no doubt I would recommend this to all coaches but I also would have liked to have worked through this program as a part of my coaching endorsement  in college.
3 Dimensional Coaching did an excellent job helping coaches realize the effect of things we often do without thinking, of the potential effect of coaching today how we were coached years ago.
Awesome!
Excellent course that if nothing else bonded us as a coaching staff. I’m excited to see how implementing some of the things we have learned will impact our program.
great course
Very effective course that gives you a different approach to coaching. Definitely learned some useful strategies and gained some insight on how to be a better coach.
This is a series about how to approach daily life vs just about coaching.
I am looking forward to implementing a new coaching strategy.
Fundamentals of coaching that every coach needs.
