I am looking forward to implementing some new strategies that i have learned in this course., especially for caches that are over 40 years old.
very helpful. has given me a better understanding.
I am looking forward to implementing some new coaching strategies that I have learned in this course. I recommend this course.... especially if you are over 40.

This has been an outstanding and refreshing course.  I have coached track and cross-country for 32 years and still truly enjoy it.  However, listening to the content of this course has given me some new perspective and zest for my coaching jobs.

I have been coaching for 32 years and was truly inspired by this course.  3D coaching dials you in on what is the most important job of a coach...that being developing athletes to be successful in all walks of life.

The 3D coaching framework is the most complete and inspiring system for growing out of traditional, single dimensional, roles. If you are interested in growing your program and your personal achievement and believe those will be measured less by wins and losses and more by character and relationships this is the program for you. Youth coaches have tremendous influence in modern society and it is critical that every coach use that influence to help create better people that will in turn create better athletes and teams.

This course has changed my outlook on how to coach my athletes in ways I could never imagine! I have developed a new purpose and gained so many helpful strategies that I can not wait to implement with my team.
I really enjoyed this program. It has opened my eyes and allowed me to put in motion the things that I like in sport back into it. This is awesome.
This course was fantastic and I enjoyed going through it step by step and using everything I learned from here on out in my career.

After teaching and coaching for 16 years... I had grown frustrated and disillusioned with "sports/sports culture."  I didn't like what I was seeing and I wasn't sure if I wanted to be apart of it anymore.  But, thanks to this journey (course) it has been a spark that ignited my passion again.  Thank you.
Very thought out.  Would recommend it to other coaches.

God put this course in my life at the right time.  I did some of these principles and activities, but I was not intentional about it.  I was a 1D coach that spent little time in the 2nd and 3rd Dimensions.  Now I know that we all need to coach the 1st Dimension, but we need to be intentional about spending time in the 2nd and 3rd Dimensions.  This is where your team really bonds together and cares for each individual on and off the field.
This course was awesome. It really opened my eyes and made think deeper on why I coach. What my true outcome is for my athletes.
This course was great , I was coaching primarily in the first dimension with some emphasis on 2nd and 3rd now I have gain more knowledge in being a better coach , a three dimensional coach.

This course completely changed me from the inside out as a coach. Before I was coaching from a standpoint of what I thought would get desired results on the wrestling mat. Now I approach coaching as impacting an athlete’s character first. The importance of skill and/or perfomance is a lot less since I took the 3Dimensional Coaching course.
Great program! As a PE teacher and coach I feel we are missing the integrity and ethics component while in competition and practice. It is our job to teach that.
Taking this course gave me more reason to buy in as a coach to be fully equip to be able to give my athletes what they need from a coach in sports and in life.
This course helped streamline my thoughts and passions of coaching and mentoring into a concise process involving strategies and goals i may never have found on my own.
Eye opening, instead of a brunch of scraps, it is organized to bring all aspects together for the benefit of the kids as well team and coach.
Coaches and Parents go over board from time to time but they need to slow down look at the bigger picture and understand what Sports teach you and this course shows that well.
Really enjoyed the stories and past experiences of former coaches.
3D was a good course to take, its provide me with some great insight in helping my player develop.
Valuable course, especially when taking it with colleagues, as we had great dialogue and conversations to help with our reflection.
I liked the class a lot. I would highly recommend it to those seeking to further their education in the coaching field.
This course could be taken 3 or 4 times and one will still gather new information or take something different each time. Loaded with knowledge and wisdom.
Its a great course for coaches who have not developed into a 3D coach and supply additional strategies for coaches who are already on their journey
It was excellent and inciteful
Outstanding course, I learned a lot and know I'll be a better coach because of this game charger 3D program.
Great course! extremely helpful

I liked the course.  It was very long and a definite time commitment.  Leaders should be advised to begin this course long before the season starts so that it can be completed before the season begins so things can really be implemented.

column3: Head Wrestling Coach - Bentonville West High School
column7: This course is life-changing. I recommend it for every coach, regardless of sport or level. If you truly want to make a difference in the lives of your athletes, take this course now!

Great course. Relies on positive thinking and action a lot. Many coaches operate at Level 1 only. Maybe we can have a summary/explanation  to give them so they can understand what they are doing wrong!

This course, although lengthy, was very beneficial and had a lot of great inspiring, thought provoking information.  A lot of aspects I am incorporating already, but I will definitely be diving deeper into that 3rd dimension to better reach my athletes as a whole.
Great way to reset your mind on coaching and life!
k bye
This Course change the way I will coach going forward.

This course reminded me of why I coach and renewed my attitude in that it's not about the first dimension, it's about shaping these athletes into outstanding adults.  It's about love, community, and integrity.  I greatly enjoyed this course and highly recommend it.
This course is both an eye opener and a check up of ones very philosophy. I highly recommend this to my friends and coaches who also desire to be life changers.
Professional and intuitive.
I LOVE 3D COACHING!

The " intentionality nature " and the results outcome at the end of this 3D coaching journey is what really made this course extraordinary. To have coaches feel that kratos moment and have them embrace it by inspiring them to formulate and write their very own transformational statement, is influence and impact at its strongest. 

The strategies made available and the tools on how to organize and plan for them is really impressive. I'm  excited to be the 3D coach I can be for my student-athletes and can't wait to start the journey to building a lifelong purposeful legacy not only for me but for out community.
This course was well worth my money. It gave me so many new ideas and perspectives to explore in my road ahead coaching.

The 3D Coaching program is a resource that every coach should take advantage of.  To be honest, I thought it would be just something to check off that I did because I was supposed to.  I've been coaching a long time and already know the benefits of some of the principles, but don't always make them a priority;  this course opened my eyes to just how important it is to connect with the kids we coach and the ideas and resources are practical, proven ways I can incorporate today.
I thought the course was very informative. There were lots of good ideas and suggestions.  I think implementing these will be very beneficial to our program.
Great course.
The helps articulate the breadth of coaching responsibilities.
Excellent course made me reevaluate my coaching techniques and philosophies.
This course was great in addressing how you as a Coach can impact student athletes on a deeper level.

I am very happy to have gone through 3D Dimensional Coaching training before my High School baseball season has gotten here! It has given me many ideas and overall just a very positive outlook on coaching and our upcoming season. I have some new strategies to implement to try to connect with our athletes.
This course was great to help me see what areas I need to improve my coaching and great examples on how I can go about implementing each dimension.

3Dimensional Coaching is a system for self-reflection and helps everyone remember the reason they do what they do.  It also provides practical, usable strategies to make a difference in the lives of everyone you come in contact with daily.
I believe the course was wonderful.  It kept me thinking and not only applying the concepts to coaching but to life as well.

I felt the course was very important in the transformation of myself as a coach.  It helped me realize that I am not alone in this process and that with a focused mindset, I will be able to transform myself into a 3rd dimension coach.
Very good information and gave me a lot to think about and ways to implement new strategies for growing my team.

column3: Greater Heights Wrestling & Oak Park High School
column7: Great insight into information I have never thought about.

This course is an excellent coaching development tool for any coach of any age and at any level.  It can be helpful in just one aspect of your coaching career or every aspect of your career depending on how you want to and plan to use it.  It is by far the best tool to help coaches get beyond the fundamental first dimension of coaching and help them to learn how to deeply impact their athletes lives at the 3rd dimensional heart level!  I am looking forward to the journey and HIGHLY recommend 3D coaching to all coaches!
This was outstanding!
Transformational is the perfect word! This program has molded me into the person I wanted to become, but had no idea how to get there. Best professional life decision I've ever made!

After 30 years of doing this basic type of coaching, this course puts it together for me. Gives me an instruction plan, confirms what have given thought to but most importantly, it fills in the gaps and answers questions that I had no answer to.

Seeing and hearing Joe Ehrmann and Jeff Duke speak many years ago during keynote presentations at coaching conventions drastically improved my coaching skills.  The 3D Institute brings together the coaching philosophies of Jeff Duke, Joe Ehrmann, and many others and teaches it to coaches worldwide so they can effectively reach the hearts and minds of athletes.  

Over the years, I have implemented many 3D strategies and every single one of them have been wildly successful in positively shaping the cultures of the teams I have coached.  Any coach who is good enough to play a sport in college can pickup on any X's and O's they need to know in a day and many can talk about the X's and O's nonstop.  However, the more challenging task is forging strong leaders and shaping organizational culture.  Coaches who really want to develop leaders must be intentional about the process and the 3D framework shows you how to do so.  

I have seen too many coaches get into the game simply because they like the X's and O's.  Not every coach I know will be willing, committed, and intentional about leadership development to the level 3D demands.  The ones who are committed and intentional about leadership development will dominate the game and beyond.  

If I am ever the Head Coach of my own football program, 3D Coaching Certification will be mandatory for all of my assistants.  It is that good.  It is that necessary.

I think this is an innovative program that helps not only new coaches, but also veteran coaches teach to & learn from the athletes that we spend so much time with. column3: Baraboo High School Head Wrestling Coach
column7: It hit all the elements of coaching in today's world and look at things in a deep spiritual sense that is far different than any training I received. I think that is why we coach and teach. It was awesome.

This course is designed for the experienced coach. It offers many suggestions that go beyond surface coaching.

This program has provided me with the tools to move forward in as a fully capable, competent and inspired 3Dimensional Coach. To be honest, many of the foundations of 3D Coaching are already in my heart. I have always coached to the hearts and to the minds of my players. However, I would not in any way have considered myself an expert within the Level 2 and Level 3 realms of coaching. I knew I wanted to coach this way. I knew I had to coach this way. I even know why I wanted to coach this way. I did not know exactly how to coach this way, though. The strategies provided through 3Dimension Coaching will benefit my girls basketball players in ways I can't even imagine. The strategies will not only make me better as a coach, but also as a person. This program should be mandatory for any coach, for any person responsible with coaching and caring for players. Thank you so, so much for this opportunity. My life, and most importantly my players' lives, will be changed forever by this!
I loved it. Showed me a variety of methods to become not just a better coach or teacher but as a person. Information was detailed perfectly while being easy to understand.

This course revolutionized everything I knew about my role as a coach. Before I took this course I was mostly a 1st dimensional coach. I knew I wanted to touch on the 2nd and 3rd dimensions, but didn't know how. This course further developed my understanding of why it's important to coach in the 2nd and 3rd dimensions and how to coach in those dimensions. In addition, the concepts I learned are not just for the athletic field, I have used them to change how I talk to my kids, what I teach them to value and how I encourage them. So, even if you're not a coach, their principles cross over to every area of your life and are something everyone should learn and know.

top notch
awesome

This is a priceless tool to help lead me and provide resources to help me succeed in the most important part of being a coach....reflecting the love of Jesus Christ.

I found it to be eye opening and transformational for me as a coach. It showed me I was on the right track and gave me insight on how put into action my thoughts

Thank you!

I learned a lot from this course.

Good job

It was an outstanding course!

it was a great course

worthwhile!

Awesome

I have always tried to teach my players about hard work, being a family, helping each other and that things (life) is not always fair. This course gives young coaches the foundation to be able to see their game in a new light, to be used for His glory. Thank you!

You have forever changed the way of coaching, hats off to all of your team!!!

I love being with the kids and developing their knowledge and skill for the game, but absolutely hate the pains that competition bring to the heart. If we can remember to focus on developing relationships and being truly "good" to one another, as Jesus taught, then we will do well:) Thank you!

column3: Head Coach/ Pella High School - Lady Dutch Soccer
column7: This course was awesome and inspires me to incorporate many of these concepts into my teams practices, season and the way I interact with my players. I thought I was doing a good job but this will take it to another level.  Thank you 3-D Coaching!

column3: 4th Kota Kinabalu Sabah Boys' Brigade Malaysia
column7: Psychology will continue to have a profound effect on our daily life for years to come. The spectrum covers a wide range of activities from international negotiation to our daily personal life. This self-paced video course provides a sound understanding approach to the 3D framework on how everyone can benefit from it. The theory is straight forward, easy to understand, and also provide the practicality to foster unity and harmony within our community. To achieve this, we must not only be aware and diligent in our words and actions but also to expose ourself to vulnerability so that we can have feedback on how to improve within ourself. With the right intention and patience, anything is possible just as true contentment is within our power.
Wow is all I can say. An eye opener for me.
It was great! Some of the quizzes were a little too tough, but overall great.

This is a course that would benefit anyone! It is perfect for coaches who are just beginning their careers to the life long coaches. Wether you are need some strategies to continue doing what you already do or to change your path completely, this is an excellent way to approach either. I look forward to my own strides with the framework, but I can't wait to see how I can mentor others with this framework.

This was very helpful, and inline with much of what I have read on my own.  I love the FCA devotions at the end of each module.  This has been an incredible recourse, and will commit to weaving in this content to the fabric of all I do.

Just three years ago I had no intent to coach let alone becoming a head coach.  Having helped coach a youth program as part of student athlete coaches giving back to build the program I was comfortable with just helping.  I soon concluded that the other coaches not only didnt have experience playing the sport they were coaching but no experience coaching other than helping for a year or two with the current program.  To add to it the head coach was over commited to other programs and state level youth programs and was looking to find a suitable replacement.  I started making notes to what we should practice and how we should condition and that led to me being asked to take the team over.  It started off well and great effort and improvement however my skills as a coach were from twenty years ago as a highschool student and more suited for highschool athelets and adult learning.  Looking back I seen what this coures considers 3D coaching but didn't really acknowledge how and why.  As I found training courses for myself and my assistant coaches I found this course and not only does it follow teachings of my professional life but what I was exposed to long ago.  The intent is not only will the assistant coaches complete the sport specific certifications I have already mandated but also work their way to completing this course to ensure we are focused on the athletes developement not just in sport but in life.  Our program is an investment in the future program not a sell out results now program.  This course along with the parents training will be the cornerstone to guiding this program and rebuilding the community.

The is a good course for those starting out on a coaching journey and gives a good background in vision based leading. The course is heavily based in football culture and fundamental Christian values including a connection with FCA, if you share these values it is a good place to start. It lacks depth of thought from different non-traditional perspectives and does not offer training on how be accepting of differences in ideology and lifestyle
This is a great course to learn ways to better communicate as coaches with today's player.

I am now in my 30th season as a coach and have a strong feeling that my coaching journey might be coming to an end. I don't know what the Lord has in mind for me, but I felt that this course might help me to still see and feel his hand at work in my professional life. Even though I've read the 3D Coaching book and have made attempts to implement its principles into to my coaching in the past, the ability to re-write a transformational purpose statement at the end of this course has helped to give me some strength and guidance for the season at hand. I appreciate the passion and wisdom that has gone into developing this course and pray that it will reach and impact many for years to come.

Along with being backed by a plethora of research.This course was not dated in any regards and addressed the current culture of athletics. The information pertained to every level of coaching, which makes this course a must for anyone pursuing a career in the field. I really appreciated the suggested activities and real world examples that were given throughout the modules. These are things I am so excited about implementing and have already started discussing with my coaching staff. Thank you so much for putting together such an incredible program!

This course has been absolutely incredible. The 3D framework is exactly what this generation of coaches need. The course has renewed my perspective as a coach and has opened my eyes to the areas where I have fallen short. The content is meaningful and applicable and the course flows smoothly. One of my favorite parts of the course is how it walks you through writing your transformational purpose statement. I am so pumped about my transformational purpose statement that I now have written (thanks to the course) that will guide my coaching. I cannot wait to start applying the strategies I have learned to my program. Well done!
